00065 /* Utility functions. */
00066 static int
00067 ospf_str2area_id (const char *str, struct in_addr *area_id, int *format)
00068 {
00069   char *endptr = NULL;
00070   unsigned long ret;
00071 
00072   /* match "A.B.C.D". */
00073   if (strchr (str, '.') != NULL)
00074     {
00075       ret = inet_aton (str, area_id);
00076       if (!ret)
00077         return -1;
00078       *format = OSPF_AREA_ID_FORMAT_ADDRESS;
00079     }
00080   /* match "<0-4294967295>". */
00081   else
00082     {
00083       ret = strtoul (str, &endptr, 10);
00084       if (*endptr != '\0' || (ret == ULONG_MAX && errno == ERANGE))
00085         return -1;
00086 
00087       area_id->s_addr = htonl (ret);
00088       *format = OSPF_AREA_ID_FORMAT_DECIMAL;
00089     }
00090 
00091   return 0;
00092 }

00095 static int
00096 str2distribute_source (const char *str, int *source)
00097 {
00098   /* Sanity check. */
00099   if (str == NULL)
00100     return 0;
00101 
00102   if (strncmp (str, "k", 1) == 0)
00103     *source = ZEBRA_ROUTE_KERNEL;
00104   else if (strncmp (str, "c", 1) == 0)
00105     *source = ZEBRA_ROUTE_CONNECT;
00106   else if (strncmp (str, "s", 1) == 0)
00107     *source = ZEBRA_ROUTE_STATIC;
00108   else if (strncmp (str, "r", 1) == 0)
00109     *source = ZEBRA_ROUTE_RIP;
00110   else if (strncmp (str, "b", 1) == 0)
00111     *source = ZEBRA_ROUTE_BGP;
00112   else
00113     return 0;
00114 
00115   return 1;
00116 }
00117 
00118 static int
00119 str2metric (const char *str, int *metric)
00120 {
00121   /* Sanity check. */
00122   if (str == NULL)
00123     return 0;
00124 
00125   *metric = strtol (str, NULL, 10);
00126   if (*metric < 0 && *metric > 16777214)
00127     {
00128       /* vty_out (vty, "OSPF metric value is invalid%s", VTY_NEWLINE); */
00129       return 0;
00130     }
00131 
00132   return 1;
00133 }
00134 
00135 static int
00136 str2metric_type (const char *str, int *metric_type)
00137 {
00138   /* Sanity check. */
00139   if (str == NULL)
00140     return 0;
00141 
00142   if (strncmp (str, "1", 1) == 0)
00143     *metric_type = EXTERNAL_METRIC_TYPE_1;
00144   else if (strncmp (str, "2", 1) == 0)
00145     *metric_type = EXTERNAL_METRIC_TYPE_2;
00146   else
00147     return 0;
00148 
00149   return 1;
00150 }

00152 int
00153 ospf_oi_count (struct interface *ifp)
00154 {
00155   struct route_node *rn;
00156   int i = 0;
00157 
00158   for (rn = route_top (IF_OIFS (ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
00159     if (rn->info)
00160       i++;
00161 
00162   return i;
00163 }

00252 static void
00253 ospf_passive_interface_default (struct ospf *ospf, u_char newval)
00254 {
00255   struct listnode *ln;
00256   struct interface *ifp;
00257   struct ospf_interface *oi;
00258   
00259   ospf->passive_interface_default = newval;
00260 
00261   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (om->iflist, ln, ifp))
00262     {
00263       if (ifp &&
00264           OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), passive_interface))
00265         UNSET_IF_PARAM (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), passive_interface);
00266     }
00267   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->oiflist, ln, oi))
00268     {
00269       if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (oi->params, passive_interface))
00270         UNSET_IF_PARAM (oi->params, passive_interface);
00271       /* update multicast memberships */
00272       ospf_if_set_multicast(oi);
00273     }
00274 }
00275 
00276 static void
00277 ospf_passive_interface_update (struct ospf *ospf, struct interface *ifp,
00278                                struct in_addr addr, 
00279                                struct ospf_if_params *params, u_char value)
00280 {
00281   u_char dflt;
00282   
00283   params->passive_interface = value;
00284   if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
00285     {
00286       if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), passive_interface))
00287         dflt = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->passive_interface;
00288       else
00289         dflt = ospf->passive_interface_default;
00290       
00291       if (value != dflt)
00292         SET_IF_PARAM (params, passive_interface);
00293       else
00294         UNSET_IF_PARAM (params, passive_interface);
00295       
00296       ospf_free_if_params (ifp, addr);
00297       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
00298     }
00299   else
00300     {
00301       if (value != ospf->passive_interface_default)
00302         SET_IF_PARAM (params, passive_interface);
00303       else
00304         UNSET_IF_PARAM (params, passive_interface);
00305     }
00306 }

00308 DEFUN (ospf_passive_interface,
00309        ospf_passive_interface_addr_cmd,
00310        "passive-interface IFNAME A.B.C.D",
00311        "Suppress routing updates on an interface\n"
00312        "Interface's name\n")
00313 {
00314   struct interface *ifp;
00315   struct in_addr addr;
00316   int ret;
00317   struct ospf_if_params *params;
00318   struct route_node *rn;
00319   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
00320 
00321   if (argc == 0)
00322     {
00323       ospf_passive_interface_default (ospf, OSPF_IF_PASSIVE);
00324       return CMD_SUCCESS;
00325     }
00326 
00327   ifp = if_get_by_name (argv[0]);
00328 
00329   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
00330 
00331   if (argc == 2)
00332     {
00333       ret = inet_aton(argv[1], &addr);
00334       if (!ret)
00335     {
00336       vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
00337            VTY_NEWLINE);
00338       return CMD_WARNING;
00339     }
00340 
00341       params = ospf_get_if_params (ifp, addr);
00342       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
00343     }
00344   ospf_passive_interface_update (ospf, ifp, addr, params, OSPF_IF_PASSIVE);
00345 
00346   /* XXX We should call ospf_if_set_multicast on exactly those
00347    * interfaces for which the passive property changed.  It is too much
00348    * work to determine this set, so we do this for every interface.
00349    * This is safe and reasonable because ospf_if_set_multicast uses a
00350    * record of joined groups to avoid systems calls if the desired
00351    * memberships match the current memership.
00352    */
00353 
00354   for (rn = route_top(IF_OIFS(ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
00355     {
00356       struct ospf_interface *oi = rn->info;
00357 
00358       if (oi && (OSPF_IF_PARAM(oi, passive_interface) == OSPF_IF_PASSIVE))
00359     ospf_if_set_multicast(oi);
00360     }
00361   /*
00362    * XXX It is not clear what state transitions the interface needs to
00363    * undergo when going from active to passive.  Fixing this will
00364    * require precise identification of interfaces having such a
00365    * transition.
00366    */
00367 
00368  return CMD_SUCCESS;
00369 }

00383 DEFUN (no_ospf_passive_interface,
00384        no_ospf_passive_interface_addr_cmd,
00385        "no passive-interface IFNAME A.B.C.D",
00386        NO_STR
00387        "Allow routing updates on an interface\n"
00388        "Interface's name\n")
00389 {
00390   struct interface *ifp;
00391   struct in_addr addr;
00392   struct ospf_if_params *params;
00393   int ret;
00394   struct route_node *rn;
00395   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
00396 
00397   if (argc == 0)
00398     {
00399       ospf_passive_interface_default (ospf, OSPF_IF_ACTIVE);
00400       return CMD_SUCCESS;
00401     }
00402     
00403   ifp = if_get_by_name (argv[0]);
00404 
00405   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
00406 
00407   if (argc == 2)
00408     {
00409       ret = inet_aton(argv[1], &addr);
00410       if (!ret)
00411     {
00412       vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
00413            VTY_NEWLINE);
00414       return CMD_WARNING;
00415     }
00416 
00417       params = ospf_lookup_if_params (ifp, addr);
00418       if (params == NULL)
00419     return CMD_SUCCESS;
00420     }
00421   ospf_passive_interface_update (ospf, ifp, addr, params, OSPF_IF_ACTIVE);
00422 
00423   /* XXX We should call ospf_if_set_multicast on exactly those
00424    * interfaces for which the passive property changed.  It is too much
00425    * work to determine this set, so we do this for every interface.
00426    * This is safe and reasonable because ospf_if_set_multicast uses a
00427    * record of joined groups to avoid systems calls if the desired
00428    * memberships match the current memership.
00429    */
00430   for (rn = route_top(IF_OIFS(ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
00431     {
00432       struct ospf_interface *oi = rn->info;
00433 
00434       if (oi && (OSPF_IF_PARAM(oi, passive_interface) == OSPF_IF_ACTIVE))
00435         ospf_if_set_multicast(oi);
00436     }
00437 
00438   return CMD_SUCCESS;
00439 }

00455 DEFUN (ospf_network_area,
00456        ospf_network_area_cmd,
00457        "network A.B.C.D/M area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>)",
00458        "Enable routing on an IP network\n"
00459        "OSPF network prefix\n"
00460        "Set the OSPF area ID\n"
00461        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"
00462        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n")
00463 {
00464   struct ospf *ospf= vty->index;
00465   struct prefix_ipv4 p;
00466   struct in_addr area_id;
00467   int ret, format;
00468 
00469   /* Get network prefix and Area ID. */
00470   VTY_GET_IPV4_PREFIX ("network prefix", p, argv[0]);
00471   VTY_GET_OSPF_AREA_ID (area_id, format, argv[1]);
00472 
00473   ret = ospf_network_set (ospf, &p, area_id);
00474   if (ret == 0)
00475     {
00476       vty_out (vty, "There is already same network statement.%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
00477       return CMD_WARNING;
00478     }
00479 
00480   return CMD_SUCCESS;
00481 }

00514 DEFUN (ospf_area_range,
00515        ospf_area_range_cmd,
00516        "area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) range A.B.C.D/M",
00517        "OSPF area parameters\n"
00518        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"
00519        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n"
00520        "Summarize routes matching address/mask (border routers only)\n"
00521        "Area range prefix\n")
00522 {
00523   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
00524   struct prefix_ipv4 p;
00525   struct in_addr area_id;
00526   int format;
00527   u_int32_t cost;
00528 
00529   VTY_GET_OSPF_AREA_ID (area_id, format, argv[0]);
00530   VTY_GET_IPV4_PREFIX ("area range", p, argv[1]);
00531 
00532   ospf_area_range_set (ospf, area_id, &p, OSPF_AREA_RANGE_ADVERTISE);
00533   if (argc > 2)
00534     {
00535       VTY_GET_INTEGER ("range cost", cost, argv[2]);
00536       ospf_area_range_cost_set (ospf, area_id, &p, cost);
00537     }
00538 
00539   return CMD_SUCCESS;
00540 }

00676   VTY_GET_IPV4_PREFIX ("substituted network prefix", s, argv[2]);
00677 
00678   ospf_area_range_substitute_set (ospf, area_id, &p, &s);
00679 
00680   return CMD_SUCCESS;
00681 }

00709 
00710 /* Command Handler Logic in VLink stuff is delicate!!
00711 
00712     ALTER AT YOUR OWN RISK!!!!
00713 
00714     Various dummy values are used to represent 'NoChange' state for
00715     VLink configuration NOT being changed by a VLink command, and
00716     special syntax is used within the command strings so that the
00717     typed in command verbs can be seen in the configuration command
00718     bacckend handler.  This is to drastically reduce the verbeage
00719     required to coe up with a reasonably compatible Cisco VLink command
00720 
00721     - Matthew Grant <grantma@anathoth.gen.nz> 
00722     Wed, 21 Feb 2001 15:13:52 +1300
00723  */
00724 
00725 
00726 /* Configuration data for virtual links 
00727  */ 
00728 struct ospf_vl_config_data {
00729   struct vty *vty;      /* vty stuff */
00730   struct in_addr area_id;   /* area ID from command line */
00731   int format;           /* command line area ID format */
00732   struct in_addr vl_peer;   /* command line vl_peer */
00733   int auth_type;        /* Authehntication type, if given */
00734   char *auth_key;       /* simple password if present */
00735   int crypto_key_id;        /* Cryptographic key ID */
00736   char *md5_key;        /* MD5 authentication key */
00737   int hello_interval;           /* Obvious what these are... */
00738   int retransmit_interval; 
00739   int transmit_delay;
00740   int dead_interval;
00741 };
00742 
00743 static void
00744 ospf_vl_config_data_init (struct ospf_vl_config_data *vl_config, 
00745               struct vty *vty)
00746 {
00747   memset (vl_config, 0, sizeof (struct ospf_vl_config_data));
00748   vl_config->auth_type = OSPF_AUTH_CMD_NOTSEEN;
00749   vl_config->vty = vty;
00750 }
00751 
00752 static struct ospf_vl_data *
00753 ospf_find_vl_data (struct ospf *ospf, struct ospf_vl_config_data *vl_config)
00754 {
00755   struct ospf_area *area;
00756   struct ospf_vl_data *vl_data;
00757   struct vty *vty;
00758   struct in_addr area_id;
00759 
00760   vty = vl_config->vty;
00761   area_id = vl_config->area_id;
00762 
00763   if (area_id.s_addr == OSPF_AREA_BACKBONE)
00764     {
00765       vty_out (vty, 
00766            "Configuring VLs over the backbone is not allowed%s",
00767                VTY_NEWLINE);
00768       return NULL;
00769     }
00770   area = ospf_area_get (ospf, area_id, vl_config->format);
00771 
00772   if (area->external_routing != OSPF_AREA_DEFAULT)
00773     {
00774       if (vl_config->format == OSPF_AREA_ID_FORMAT_ADDRESS)
00775     vty_out (vty, "Area %s is %s%s",
00776          inet_ntoa (area_id),
00777          area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_NSSA?"nssa":"stub",
00778          VTY_NEWLINE);
00779       else
00780     vty_out (vty, "Area %ld is %s%s",
00781          (u_long)ntohl (area_id.s_addr),
00782          area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_NSSA?"nssa":"stub",
00783          VTY_NEWLINE);  
00784       return NULL;
00785     }
00786   
00787   if ((vl_data = ospf_vl_lookup (ospf, area, vl_config->vl_peer)) == NULL)
00788     {
00789       vl_data = ospf_vl_data_new (area, vl_config->vl_peer);
00790       if (vl_data->vl_oi == NULL)
00791     {
00792       vl_data->vl_oi = ospf_vl_new (ospf, vl_data);
00793       ospf_vl_add (ospf, vl_data);
00794       ospf_spf_calculate_schedule (ospf);
00795     }
00796     }
00797   return vl_data;
00798 }
00799 
00800 
00801 static int
00802 ospf_vl_set_security (struct ospf_vl_data *vl_data,
00803               struct ospf_vl_config_data *vl_config)
00804 {
00805   struct crypt_key *ck;
00806   struct vty *vty;
00807   struct interface *ifp = vl_data->vl_oi->ifp;
00808 
00809   vty = vl_config->vty;
00810 
00811   if (vl_config->auth_type != OSPF_AUTH_CMD_NOTSEEN)
00812     {
00813       SET_IF_PARAM (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), auth_type);
00814       IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->auth_type = vl_config->auth_type;
00815     }
00816 
00817   if (vl_config->auth_key)
00818     {
00819       memset(IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->auth_simple, 0, OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE_SIZE+1);
00820       strncpy ((char *) IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->auth_simple, vl_config->auth_key, 
00821            OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE_SIZE);
00822     }
00823   else if (vl_config->md5_key)
00824     {
00825       if (ospf_crypt_key_lookup (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->auth_crypt, vl_config->crypto_key_id) 
00826       != NULL)
00827     {
00828       vty_out (vty, "OSPF: Key %d already exists%s",
00829            vl_config->crypto_key_id, VTY_NEWLINE);
00830       return CMD_WARNING;
00831     }
00832       ck = ospf_crypt_key_new ();
00833       ck->key_id = vl_config->crypto_key_id;
00834       memset(ck->auth_key, 0, OSPF_AUTH_MD5_SIZE+1);
00835       strncpy ((char *) ck->auth_key, vl_config->md5_key, OSPF_AUTH_MD5_SIZE);
00836       
00837       ospf_crypt_key_add (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->auth_crypt, ck);
00838     }
00839   else if (vl_config->crypto_key_id != 0)
00840     {
00841       /* Delete a key */
00842 
00843       if (ospf_crypt_key_lookup (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->auth_crypt, 
00844                  vl_config->crypto_key_id) == NULL)
00845     {
00846       vty_out (vty, "OSPF: Key %d does not exist%s", 
00847            vl_config->crypto_key_id, VTY_NEWLINE);
00848       return CMD_WARNING;
00849     }
00850       
00851       ospf_crypt_key_delete (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->auth_crypt, vl_config->crypto_key_id);
00852 
00853     }
00854   
00855   return CMD_SUCCESS;
00856 }
00857 
00858 static int
00859 ospf_vl_set_timers (struct ospf_vl_data *vl_data,
00860             struct ospf_vl_config_data *vl_config)
00861 {
00862   struct interface *ifp = ifp = vl_data->vl_oi->ifp;
00863   /* Virtual Link data initialised to defaults, so only set
00864      if a value given */
00865   if (vl_config->hello_interval)
00866     {
00867       SET_IF_PARAM (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), v_hello);
00868       IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->v_hello = vl_config->hello_interval;
00869     }
00870 
00871   if (vl_config->dead_interval)
00872     {
00873       SET_IF_PARAM (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), v_wait);
00874       IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->v_wait = vl_config->dead_interval;
00875     }
00876 
00877   if (vl_config->retransmit_interval)
00878     {
00879       SET_IF_PARAM (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), retransmit_interval);
00880       IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->retransmit_interval = vl_config->retransmit_interval;
00881     }
00882   
00883   if (vl_config->transmit_delay)
00884     {
00885       SET_IF_PARAM (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), transmit_delay);
00886       IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->transmit_delay = vl_config->transmit_delay;
00887     }
00888   
00889   return CMD_SUCCESS;
00890 }
00891 
00892 
00893 
00894 /* The business end of all of the above */
00895 static int
00896 ospf_vl_set (struct ospf *ospf, struct ospf_vl_config_data *vl_config)
00897 {
00898   struct ospf_vl_data *vl_data;
00899   int ret;
00900 
00901   vl_data = ospf_find_vl_data (ospf, vl_config);
00902   if (!vl_data)
00903     return CMD_WARNING;
00904   
00905   /* Process this one first as it can have a fatal result, which can
00906      only logically occur if the virtual link exists already
00907      Thus a command error does not result in a change to the
00908      running configuration such as unexpectedly altered timer 
00909      values etc.*/
00910   ret = ospf_vl_set_security (vl_data, vl_config);
00911   if (ret != CMD_SUCCESS)
00912     return ret;
00913 
00914   /* Set any time based parameters, these area already range checked */
00915 
00916   ret = ospf_vl_set_timers (vl_data, vl_config);
00917   if (ret != CMD_SUCCESS)
00918     return ret;
00919 
00920   return CMD_SUCCESS;
00921 
00922 }

00924 /* This stuff exists to make specifying all the alias commands A LOT simpler
00925  */
00926 #define VLINK_HELPSTR_IPADDR \
00927        "OSPF area parameters\n" \
00928        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n" \
00929        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n" \
00930        "Configure a virtual link\n" \
00931        "Router ID of the remote ABR\n"
00932 
00933 #define VLINK_HELPSTR_AUTHTYPE_SIMPLE \
00934        "Enable authentication on this virtual link\n" \
00935        "dummy string \n" 
00936 
00937 #define VLINK_HELPSTR_AUTHTYPE_ALL \
00938        VLINK_HELPSTR_AUTHTYPE_SIMPLE \
00939        "Use null authentication\n" \
00940        "Use message-digest authentication\n"
00941 
00942 #define VLINK_HELPSTR_TIME_PARAM_NOSECS \
00943        "Time between HELLO packets\n" \
00944        "Time between retransmitting lost link state advertisements\n" \
00945        "Link state transmit delay\n" \
00946        "Interval after which a neighbor is declared dead\n"
00947 
00948 #define VLINK_HELPSTR_TIME_PARAM \
00949        VLINK_HELPSTR_TIME_PARAM_NOSECS \
00950        "Seconds\n"
00951 
00952 #define VLINK_HELPSTR_AUTH_SIMPLE \
00953        "Authentication password (key)\n" \
00954        "The OSPF password (key)"
00955 
00956 #define VLINK_HELPSTR_AUTH_MD5 \
00957        "Message digest authentication password (key)\n" \
00958        "dummy string \n" \
00959        "Key ID\n" \
00960        "Use MD5 algorithm\n" \
00961        "The OSPF password (key)"
00962 
00963 DEFUN (ospf_area_vlink,
00964        ospf_area_vlink_cmd,
00965        "area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) virtual-link A.B.C.D",
00966        VLINK_HELPSTR_IPADDR)
00967 {
00968   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
00969   struct ospf_vl_config_data vl_config;
00970   char auth_key[OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE_SIZE+1];
00971   char md5_key[OSPF_AUTH_MD5_SIZE+1]; 
00972   int i;
00973   int ret;
00974   
00975   ospf_vl_config_data_init(&vl_config, vty);
00976 
00977   /* Read off first 2 parameters and check them */
00978   ret = ospf_str2area_id (argv[0], &vl_config.area_id, &vl_config.format);
00979   if (ret < 0)
00980     {
00981       vty_out (vty, "OSPF area ID is invalid%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
00982       return CMD_WARNING;
00983     }
00984 
00985   ret = inet_aton (argv[1], &vl_config.vl_peer);
00986   if (! ret)
00987     {
00988       vty_out (vty, "Please specify valid Router ID as a.b.c.d%s",
00989                VTY_NEWLINE);
00990       return CMD_WARNING;
00991     }
00992 
00993   if (argc <=2)
00994     {
00995       /* Thats all folks! - BUGS B. strikes again!!!*/
00996 
00997       return  ospf_vl_set (ospf, &vl_config);
00998     }
00999 
01000   /* Deal with other parameters */
01001   for (i=2; i < argc; i++)
01002     {
01003 
01004       /* vty_out (vty, "argv[%d] - %s%s", i, argv[i], VTY_NEWLINE); */
01005 
01006       switch (argv[i][0])
01007     {
01008 
01009     case 'a':
01010       if (i > 2 || strncmp (argv[i], "authentication-", 15) == 0)
01011         {
01012           /* authentication-key - this option can occur anywhere on 
01013                               command line.  At start of command line
01014                       must check for authentication option. */
01015           memset (auth_key, 0, OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE_SIZE + 1);
01016           strncpy (auth_key, argv[i+1], OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE_SIZE);
01017           vl_config.auth_key = auth_key;
01018           i++;
01019         }
01020       else if (strncmp (argv[i], "authentication", 14) == 0)
01021         {
01022           /* authentication  - this option can only occur at start
01023                            of command line */
01024           vl_config.auth_type = OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE;
01025           if ((i+1) < argc)
01026         {
01027           if (strncmp (argv[i+1], "n", 1) == 0)
01028             {
01029               /* "authentication null" */
01030               vl_config.auth_type = OSPF_AUTH_NULL;
01031               i++;
01032             }
01033           else if (strncmp (argv[i+1], "m", 1) == 0
01034                && strcmp (argv[i+1], "message-digest-") != 0)
01035             {
01036               /* "authentication message-digest" */ 
01037               vl_config.auth_type = OSPF_AUTH_CRYPTOGRAPHIC;
01038               i++;
01039             }
01040         }
01041         }
01042       break;
01043 
01044     case 'm':
01045       /* message-digest-key */
01046       i++;
01047       vl_config.crypto_key_id = strtol (argv[i], NULL, 10);
01048       if (vl_config.crypto_key_id < 0)
01049         return CMD_WARNING;
01050       i++;
01051       memset(md5_key, 0, OSPF_AUTH_MD5_SIZE+1);
01052       strncpy (md5_key, argv[i], OSPF_AUTH_MD5_SIZE);
01053       vl_config.md5_key = md5_key; 
01054       break;
01055 
01056     case 'h':
01057       /* Hello interval */
01058       i++;
01059       vl_config.hello_interval = strtol (argv[i], NULL, 10);
01060       if (vl_config.hello_interval < 0) 
01061         return CMD_WARNING;
01062       break;
01063 
01064     case 'r':
01065       /* Retransmit Interval */
01066       i++;
01067       vl_config.retransmit_interval = strtol (argv[i], NULL, 10);
01068       if (vl_config.retransmit_interval < 0)
01069         return CMD_WARNING;
01070       break;
01071 
01072     case 't':
01073       /* Transmit Delay */
01074       i++;
01075       vl_config.transmit_delay = strtol (argv[i], NULL, 10);
01076       if (vl_config.transmit_delay < 0)
01077         return CMD_WARNING;
01078       break;
01079 
01080     case 'd':
01081       /* Dead Interval */
01082       i++;
01083       vl_config.dead_interval = strtol (argv[i], NULL, 10);
01084       if (vl_config.dead_interval < 0)
01085         return CMD_WARNING;
01086       break;
01087     }
01088     }
01089 
01090 
01091   /* Action configuration */
01092 
01093   return ospf_vl_set (ospf, &vl_config);
01094 
01095 }
01096 
01097 DEFUN (no_ospf_area_vlink,
01098        no_ospf_area_vlink_cmd,
01099        "no area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) virtual-link A.B.C.D",
01100        NO_STR
01101        VLINK_HELPSTR_IPADDR)
01102 {
01103   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
01104   struct ospf_area *area;
01105   struct ospf_vl_config_data vl_config;
01106   struct ospf_vl_data *vl_data = NULL;
01107   char auth_key[OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE_SIZE+1];
01108   int i;
01109   int ret, format;
01110 
01111   ospf_vl_config_data_init(&vl_config, vty);
01112 
01113   ret = ospf_str2area_id (argv[0], &vl_config.area_id, &format);
01114   if (ret < 0)
01115     {
01116       vty_out (vty, "OSPF area ID is invalid%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
01117       return CMD_WARNING;
01118     }
01119 
01120   area = ospf_area_lookup_by_area_id (ospf, vl_config.area_id);
01121   if (!area)
01122     {
01123       vty_out (vty, "Area does not exist%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
01124       return CMD_WARNING;
01125     }
01126 
01127   ret = inet_aton (argv[1], &vl_config.vl_peer);
01128   if (! ret)
01129     {
01130       vty_out (vty, "Please specify valid Router ID as a.b.c.d%s",
01131                VTY_NEWLINE);
01132       return CMD_WARNING;
01133     }
01134 
01135   if (argc <=2)
01136     {
01137       /* Basic VLink no command */
01138       /* Thats all folks! - BUGS B. strikes again!!!*/
01139       if ((vl_data = ospf_vl_lookup (ospf, area, vl_config.vl_peer)))
01140     ospf_vl_delete (ospf, vl_data);
01141 
01142       ospf_area_check_free (ospf, vl_config.area_id);
01143       
01144       return CMD_SUCCESS;
01145     }
01146 
01147   /* If we are down here, we are reseting parameters */
01148 
01149   /* Deal with other parameters */
01150   for (i=2; i < argc; i++)
01151     {
01152       /* vty_out (vty, "argv[%d] - %s%s", i, argv[i], VTY_NEWLINE); */
01153 
01154       switch (argv[i][0])
01155     {
01156 
01157     case 'a':
01158       if (i > 2 || strncmp (argv[i], "authentication-", 15) == 0)
01159         {
01160           /* authentication-key - this option can occur anywhere on 
01161                               command line.  At start of command line
01162                       must check for authentication option. */
01163           memset (auth_key, 0, OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE_SIZE + 1);
01164           vl_config.auth_key = auth_key;
01165         }
01166       else if (strncmp (argv[i], "authentication", 14) == 0)
01167         {
01168           /* authentication  - this option can only occur at start
01169                            of command line */
01170           vl_config.auth_type = OSPF_AUTH_NOTSET;
01171         }
01172       break;
01173 
01174     case 'm':
01175       /* message-digest-key */
01176       /* Delete one key */
01177       i++;
01178       vl_config.crypto_key_id = strtol (argv[i], NULL, 10);
01179       if (vl_config.crypto_key_id < 0)
01180         return CMD_WARNING;
01181       vl_config.md5_key = NULL; 
01182       break;
01183 
01184     case 'h':
01185       /* Hello interval */
01186       vl_config.hello_interval = OSPF_HELLO_INTERVAL_DEFAULT;
01187       break;
01188 
01189     case 'r':
01190       /* Retransmit Interval */
01191       vl_config.retransmit_interval = OSPF_RETRANSMIT_INTERVAL_DEFAULT;
01192       break;
01193 
01194     case 't':
01195       /* Transmit Delay */
01196       vl_config.transmit_delay = OSPF_TRANSMIT_DELAY_DEFAULT;
01197       break;
01198 
01199     case 'd':
01200       /* Dead Interval */
01201       i++;
01202       vl_config.dead_interval = OSPF_ROUTER_DEAD_INTERVAL_DEFAULT;
01203       break;
01204     }
01205     }
01206 
01207 
01208   /* Action configuration */
01209 
01210   return ospf_vl_set (ospf, &vl_config);
01211 }

01213 ALIAS (ospf_area_vlink,

01406 DEFUN (ospf_area_shortcut,
01407        ospf_area_shortcut_cmd,
01408        "area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) shortcut (default|enable|disable)",
01409        "OSPF area parameters\n"
01410        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"
01411        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n"
01412        "Configure the area's shortcutting mode\n"
01413        "Set default shortcutting behavior\n"
01414        "Enable shortcutting through the area\n"
01415        "Disable shortcutting through the area\n")
01416 {
01417   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
01418   struct ospf_area *area;
01419   struct in_addr area_id;
01420   int mode;
01421   int format;
01422 
01423   VTY_GET_OSPF_AREA_ID_NO_BB ("shortcut", area_id, format, argv[0]);
01424 
01425   area = ospf_area_get (ospf, area_id, format);
01426 
01427   if (strncmp (argv[1], "de", 2) == 0)
01428     mode = OSPF_SHORTCUT_DEFAULT;
01429   else if (strncmp (argv[1], "di", 2) == 0)
01430     mode = OSPF_SHORTCUT_DISABLE;
01431   else if (strncmp (argv[1], "e", 1) == 0)
01432     mode = OSPF_SHORTCUT_ENABLE;
01433   else
01434     return CMD_WARNING;
01435 
01436   ospf_area_shortcut_set (ospf, area, mode);
01437 
01438   if (ospf->abr_type != OSPF_ABR_SHORTCUT)
01439     vty_out (vty, "Shortcut area setting will take effect "
01440          "only when the router is configured as Shortcut ABR%s",
01441          VTY_NEWLINE);
01442 
01443   return CMD_SUCCESS;
01444 }
01445 
01446 DEFUN (no_ospf_area_shortcut,
01447        no_ospf_area_shortcut_cmd,
01448        "no area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) shortcut (enable|disable)",
01449        NO_STR
01450        "OSPF area parameters\n"
01451        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"
01452        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n"
01453        "Deconfigure the area's shortcutting mode\n"
01454        "Deconfigure enabled shortcutting through the area\n"
01455        "Deconfigure disabled shortcutting through the area\n")
01456 {
01457   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
01458   struct ospf_area *area;
01459   struct in_addr area_id;
01460   int format;
01461 
01462   VTY_GET_OSPF_AREA_ID_NO_BB ("shortcut", area_id, format, argv[0]);
01463 
01464   area = ospf_area_lookup_by_area_id (ospf, area_id);
01465   if (!area)
01466     return CMD_SUCCESS;
01467 
01468   ospf_area_shortcut_unset (ospf, area);
01469 
01470   return CMD_SUCCESS;
01471 }

01475        ospf_area_stub_cmd,
01476        "area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) stub",
01477        "OSPF area parameters\n"
01478        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"
01479        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n"
01480        "Configure OSPF area as stub\n")
01481 {

01570 static int
01571 ospf_area_nssa_cmd_handler (struct vty *vty, int argc, const char *argv[], 
01572                             int nosum)
01573 {
01574   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
01575   struct in_addr area_id;
01576   int ret, format;
01577 
01578   VTY_GET_OSPF_AREA_ID_NO_BB ("NSSA", area_id, format, argv[0]);
01579 
01580   ret = ospf_area_nssa_set (ospf, area_id);
01581   if (ret == 0)
01582     {
01583       vty_out (vty, "%% Area cannot be nssa as it contains a virtual link%s",
01584            VTY_NEWLINE);
01585       return CMD_WARNING;
01586     }
01587 
01588   if (argc > 1)
01589     {
01590       if (strncmp (argv[1], "translate-c", 11) == 0)
01591         ospf_area_nssa_translator_role_set (ospf, area_id,
01592                         OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_CANDIDATE);
01593       else if (strncmp (argv[1], "translate-n", 11) == 0)
01594         ospf_area_nssa_translator_role_set (ospf, area_id,
01595                         OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_NEVER);
01596       else if (strncmp (argv[1], "translate-a", 11) == 0)
01597         ospf_area_nssa_translator_role_set (ospf, area_id,
01598                         OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_ALWAYS);
01599     }
01600   else
01601     {
01602       ospf_area_nssa_translator_role_set (ospf, area_id,
01603                         OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_CANDIDATE);
01604     }
01605 
01606   if (nosum)
01607     ospf_area_no_summary_set (ospf, area_id);
01608   else
01609     ospf_area_no_summary_unset (ospf, area_id);
01610 
01611   ospf_schedule_abr_task (ospf);
01612     
01613   return CMD_SUCCESS;
01614 }
01615 
01616 DEFUN (ospf_area_nssa_translate_no_summary,
01617        ospf_area_nssa_translate_no_summary_cmd,
01618        "area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) nssa (translate-candidate|translate-never|translate-always) no-summary",
01619        "OSPF area parameters\n"
01620        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"

01711 DEFUN (ospf_area_default_cost,
01712        ospf_area_default_cost_cmd,
01713        "area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) default-cost <0-16777215>",
01714        "OSPF area parameters\n"
01715        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"
01716        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n"
01717        "Set the summary-default cost of a NSSA or stub area\n"
01718        "Stub's advertised default summary cost\n")
01719 {
01720   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
01721   struct ospf_area *area;
01722   struct in_addr area_id;
01723   u_int32_t cost;
01724   int format;
01725   struct prefix_ipv4 p;
01726 
01727   VTY_GET_OSPF_AREA_ID_NO_BB ("default-cost", area_id, format, argv[0]);
01728   VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("stub default cost", cost, argv[1], 0, 16777215);
01729 
01730   area = ospf_area_get (ospf, area_id, format);
01731 
01732   if (area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_DEFAULT)
01733     {
01734       vty_out (vty, "The area is neither stub, nor NSSA%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
01735       return CMD_WARNING;
01736     }
01737 
01738   area->default_cost = cost;
01739 
01740   p.family = AF_INET;
01741   p.prefix.s_addr = OSPF_DEFAULT_DESTINATION;
01742   p.prefixlen = 0;
01743   if (IS_DEBUG_OSPF_EVENT)
01744     zlog_debug ("ospf_abr_announce_stub_defaults(): "
01745                 "announcing 0.0.0.0/0 to area %s",
01746                inet_ntoa (area->area_id));
01747   ospf_abr_announce_network_to_area (&p, area->default_cost, area);
01748 
01749   return CMD_SUCCESS;
01750 }
01751 
01752 DEFUN (no_ospf_area_default_cost,
01753        no_ospf_area_default_cost_cmd,
01754        "no area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) default-cost <0-16777215>",
01755        NO_STR
01756        "OSPF area parameters\n"
01757        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"
01758        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n"
01759        "Set the summary-default cost of a NSSA or stub area\n"
01760        "Stub's advertised default summary cost\n")
01761 {
01762   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
01763   struct ospf_area *area;
01764   struct in_addr area_id;
01765   u_int32_t cost;
01766   int format;
01767   struct prefix_ipv4 p;
01768 
01769   VTY_GET_OSPF_AREA_ID_NO_BB ("default-cost", area_id, format, argv[0]);
01770   VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("stub default cost", cost, argv[1], 0, 16777215);
01771 
01772   area = ospf_area_lookup_by_area_id (ospf, area_id);
01773   if (area == NULL)
01774     return CMD_SUCCESS;
01775 
01776   if (area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_DEFAULT)
01777     {
01778       vty_out (vty, "The area is neither stub, nor NSSA%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
01779       return CMD_WARNING;
01780     }
01781 
01782   area->default_cost = 1;
01783 
01784   p.family = AF_INET;
01785   p.prefix.s_addr = OSPF_DEFAULT_DESTINATION;
01786   p.prefixlen = 0;
01787   if (IS_DEBUG_OSPF_EVENT)
01788     zlog_debug ("ospf_abr_announce_stub_defaults(): "
01789                 "announcing 0.0.0.0/0 to area %s",
01790                inet_ntoa (area->area_id));
01791   ospf_abr_announce_network_to_area (&p, area->default_cost, area);
01792 
01793 
01794   ospf_area_check_free (ospf, area_id);
01795 
01796   return CMD_SUCCESS;
01797 }

01896 DEFUN (ospf_area_filter_list,
01897        ospf_area_filter_list_cmd,
01898        "area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) filter-list prefix WORD (in|out)",
01899        "OSPF area parameters\n"
01900        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"
01901        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n"
01902        "Filter networks between OSPF areas\n"
01903        "Filter prefixes between OSPF areas\n"
01904        "Name of an IP prefix-list\n"
01905        "Filter networks sent to this area\n"
01906        "Filter networks sent from this area\n")
01907 {
01908   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
01909   struct ospf_area *area;
01910   struct in_addr area_id;
01911   struct prefix_list *plist;
01912   int format;
01913 
01914   VTY_GET_OSPF_AREA_ID (area_id, format, argv[0]);
01915 
01916   area = ospf_area_get (ospf, area_id, format);
01917   plist = prefix_list_lookup (AFI_IP, argv[1]);
01918   if (strncmp (argv[2], "in", 2) == 0)
01919     {
01920       PREFIX_LIST_IN (area) = plist;
01921       if (PREFIX_NAME_IN (area))
01922     free (PREFIX_NAME_IN (area));
01923 
01924       PREFIX_NAME_IN (area) = strdup (argv[1]);
01925       ospf_schedule_abr_task (ospf);
01926     }
01927   else
01928     {
01929       PREFIX_LIST_OUT (area) = plist;
01930       if (PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area))
01931     free (PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area));
01932 
01933       PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area) = strdup (argv[1]);
01934       ospf_schedule_abr_task (ospf);
01935     }
01936 
01937   return CMD_SUCCESS;
01938 }
01939 
01940 DEFUN (no_ospf_area_filter_list,
01941        no_ospf_area_filter_list_cmd,
01942        "no area (A.B.C.D|<0-4294967295>) filter-list prefix WORD (in|out)",
01943        NO_STR
01944        "OSPF area parameters\n"
01945        "OSPF area ID in IP address format\n"
01946        "OSPF area ID as a decimal value\n"
01947        "Filter networks between OSPF areas\n"
01948        "Filter prefixes between OSPF areas\n"
01949        "Name of an IP prefix-list\n"
01950        "Filter networks sent to this area\n"
01951        "Filter networks sent from this area\n")
01952 {
01953   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
01954   struct ospf_area *area;
01955   struct in_addr area_id;
01956   struct prefix_list *plist;
01957   int format;
01958 
01959   VTY_GET_OSPF_AREA_ID (area_id, format, argv[0]);
01960 
01961   if ((area = ospf_area_lookup_by_area_id (ospf, area_id)) == NULL)
01962     return CMD_SUCCESS;
01963   
01964   plist = prefix_list_lookup (AFI_IP, argv[1]);
01965   if (strncmp (argv[2], "in", 2) == 0)
01966     {
01967       if (PREFIX_NAME_IN (area))
01968     if (strcmp (PREFIX_NAME_IN (area), argv[1]) != 0)
01969       return CMD_SUCCESS;
01970 
01971       PREFIX_LIST_IN (area) = NULL;
01972       if (PREFIX_NAME_IN (area))
01973     free (PREFIX_NAME_IN (area));
01974 
01975       PREFIX_NAME_IN (area) = NULL;
01976 
01977       ospf_schedule_abr_task (ospf);
01978     }
01979   else
01980     {
01981       if (PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area))
01982     if (strcmp (PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area), argv[1]) != 0)
01983       return CMD_SUCCESS;
01984 
01985       PREFIX_LIST_OUT (area) = NULL;
01986       if (PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area))
01987     free (PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area));
01988 
01989       PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area) = NULL;
01990 
01991       ospf_schedule_abr_task (ospf);
01992     }
01993 
01994   return CMD_SUCCESS;
01995 }

02066 
02067 DEFUN (ospf_abr_type,
02068        ospf_abr_type_cmd,
02069        "ospf abr-type (cisco|ibm|shortcut|standard)",
02070        "OSPF specific commands\n"
02071        "Set OSPF ABR type\n"
02072        "Alternative ABR, cisco implementation\n"
02073        "Alternative ABR, IBM implementation\n"
02074        "Shortcut ABR\n"
02075        "Standard behavior (RFC2328)\n")
02076 {
02077   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
02078   u_char abr_type = OSPF_ABR_UNKNOWN;
02079 
02080   if (strncmp (argv[0], "c", 1) == 0)
02081     abr_type = OSPF_ABR_CISCO;
02082   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "i", 1) == 0)
02083     abr_type = OSPF_ABR_IBM;
02084   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "sh", 2) == 0)
02085     abr_type = OSPF_ABR_SHORTCUT;
02086   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "st", 2) == 0)
02087     abr_type = OSPF_ABR_STAND;
02088   else
02089     return CMD_WARNING;
02090 
02091   /* If ABR type value is changed, schedule ABR task. */
02092   if (ospf->abr_type != abr_type)
02093     {
02094       ospf->abr_type = abr_type;
02095       ospf_schedule_abr_task (ospf);
02096     }
02097 
02098   return CMD_SUCCESS;
02099 }
02100

02106        "Set OSPF ABR type\n"

02109        "Shortcut ABR\n")

02116   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "i", 1) == 0)

02119     abr_type = OSPF_ABR_SHORTCUT;
02120   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "st", 2) == 0)
02121     abr_type = OSPF_ABR_STAND;
02122   else
02123     return CMD_WARNING;
02124

02230 
02231 static int
02232 ospf_timers_spf_set (struct vty *vty, unsigned int delay,
02233                      unsigned int hold,
02234                      unsigned int max)
02235 {
02236   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
02237   
02238   ospf->spf_delay = delay;
02239   ospf->spf_holdtime = hold;
02240   ospf->spf_max_holdtime = max;
02241   
02242   return CMD_SUCCESS;
02243 }
02244 
02245 DEFUN (ospf_timers_throttle_spf,
02246        ospf_timers_throttle_spf_cmd,
02247        "timers throttle spf <0-600000> <0-600000> <0-600000>",
02248        "Adjust routing timers\n"
02249        "Throttling adaptive timer\n"
02250        "OSPF SPF timers\n"
02251        "Delay (msec) from first change received till SPF calculation\n"
02252        "Initial hold time (msec) between consecutive SPF calculations\n"
02253        "Maximum hold time (msec)\n")
02254 {
02255   unsigned int delay, hold, max;
02256   
02257   if (argc != 3)
02258     {
02259       vty_out (vty, "Insufficient arguments%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02260       return CMD_WARNING;
02261     }
02262   
02263   VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("SPF delay timer", delay, argv[0], 0, 600000);
02264   VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("SPF hold timer", hold, argv[1], 0, 600000);
02265   VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("SPF max-hold timer", max, argv[2], 0, 600000);
02266   
02267   return ospf_timers_spf_set (vty, delay, hold, max);
02268 }
02269 
02270 DEFUN_DEPRECATED (ospf_timers_spf,
02271        ospf_timers_spf_cmd,
02272        "timers spf <0-4294967295> <0-4294967295>",
02273        "Adjust routing timers\n"
02274        "OSPF SPF timers\n"
02275        "Delay (s) between receiving a change to SPF calculation\n"
02276        "Hold time (s) between consecutive SPF calculations\n")
02277 {
02278   unsigned int delay, hold;
02279   
02280   if (argc != 2)
02281     {
02282       vty_out (vty, "Insufficient number of arguments%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02283       return CMD_WARNING;
02284     }
02285   
02286   VTY_GET_INTEGER ("SPF delay timer", delay, argv[0]);
02287   VTY_GET_INTEGER ("SPF hold timer", hold, argv[1]);
02288   
02289   /* truncate down the second values if they're greater than 600000ms */
02290   if (delay > (600000 / 1000))
02291     delay = 600000;
02292   else if (delay == 0)
02293     /* 0s delay was probably specified because of lack of ms resolution */
02294     delay = OSPF_SPF_DELAY_DEFAULT;
02295   if (hold > (600000 / 1000))
02296     hold = 600000;
02297       
02298   return ospf_timers_spf_set (vty, delay * 1000, hold * 1000, hold * 1000);
02299 }
02300 
02301 DEFUN (no_ospf_timers_throttle_spf,
02302        no_ospf_timers_throttle_spf_cmd,
02303        "no timers throttle spf",
02304        NO_STR
02305        "Adjust routing timers\n"
02306        "Throttling adaptive timer\n"
02307        "OSPF SPF timers\n")
02308 {
02309   return ospf_timers_spf_set (vty,
02310                               OSPF_SPF_DELAY_DEFAULT,
02311                               OSPF_SPF_HOLDTIME_DEFAULT,
02312                               OSPF_SPF_MAX_HOLDTIME_DEFAULT);
02313 }
02314 
02315 ALIAS_DEPRECATED (no_ospf_timers_throttle_spf,
02316                   no_ospf_timers_spf_cmd,
02317                   "no timers spf",
02318                   NO_STR
02319                   "Adjust routing timers\n"
02320                   "OSPF SPF timers\n")
02321 
02322 DEFUN (ospf_neighbor,
02323        ospf_neighbor_cmd,
02324        "neighbor A.B.C.D",
02325        NEIGHBOR_STR
02326        "Neighbor IP address\n")
02327 {
02328   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
02329   struct in_addr nbr_addr;
02330   unsigned int priority = OSPF_NEIGHBOR_PRIORITY_DEFAULT;
02331   unsigned int interval = OSPF_POLL_INTERVAL_DEFAULT;
02332

02334 
02335   if (argc > 1)
02336     VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("neighbor priority", priority, argv[1], 0, 255);
02337 
02338   if (argc > 2)
02339     VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("poll interval", interval, argv[2], 1, 65535);
02340 
02341   ospf_nbr_nbma_set (ospf, nbr_addr);
02342   if (argc > 1)
02343     ospf_nbr_nbma_priority_set (ospf, nbr_addr, priority);
02344   if (argc > 2)
02345     ospf_nbr_nbma_poll_interval_set (ospf, nbr_addr, priority);
02346 
02347   return CMD_SUCCESS;
02348 }

02456 DEFUN (ospf_refresh_timer, ospf_refresh_timer_cmd,
02457        "refresh timer <10-1800>",
02458        "Adjust refresh parameters\n"
02459        "Set refresh timer\n"
02460        "Timer value in seconds\n")
02461 {
02462   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
02463   unsigned int interval;
02464   
02465   VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("refresh timer", interval, argv[0], 10, 1800);
02466   interval = (interval / 10) * 10;
02467 
02468   ospf_timers_refresh_set (ospf, interval);
02469 
02470   return CMD_SUCCESS;
02471 }
02472 
02473 DEFUN (no_ospf_refresh_timer, no_ospf_refresh_timer_val_cmd,
02474        "no refresh timer <10-1800>",
02475        "Adjust refresh parameters\n"
02476        "Unset refresh timer\n"
02477        "Timer value in seconds\n")
02478 {
02479   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
02480   unsigned int interval;
02481 
02482   if (argc == 1)
02483     {
02484       VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("refresh timer", interval, argv[0], 10, 1800);
02485   
02486       if (ospf->lsa_refresh_interval != interval ||
02487       interval == OSPF_LSA_REFRESH_INTERVAL_DEFAULT)
02488     return CMD_SUCCESS;
02489     }
02490 
02491   ospf_timers_refresh_unset (ospf);
02492 
02493   return CMD_SUCCESS;
02494 }

02502 DEFUN (ospf_auto_cost_reference_bandwidth,
02503        ospf_auto_cost_reference_bandwidth_cmd,
02504        "auto-cost reference-bandwidth <1-4294967>",
02505        "Calculate OSPF interface cost according to bandwidth\n"
02506        "Use reference bandwidth method to assign OSPF cost\n"
02507        "The reference bandwidth in terms of Mbits per second\n")
02508 {
02509   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
02510   u_int32_t refbw;
02511   struct listnode *node;
02512   struct interface *ifp;
02513 
02514   refbw = strtol (argv[0], NULL, 10);
02515   if (refbw < 1 || refbw > 4294967)
02516     {
02517       vty_out (vty, "reference-bandwidth value is invalid%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02518       return CMD_WARNING;
02519     }
02520 
02521   /* If reference bandwidth is changed. */
02522   if ((refbw * 1000) == ospf->ref_bandwidth)
02523     return CMD_SUCCESS;
02524   
02525   ospf->ref_bandwidth = refbw * 1000;
02526   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (om->iflist, node, ifp))
02527     ospf_if_recalculate_output_cost (ifp);
02528   
02529   return CMD_SUCCESS;
02530 }
02531 
02532 DEFUN (no_ospf_auto_cost_reference_bandwidth,
02533        no_ospf_auto_cost_reference_bandwidth_cmd,
02534        "no auto-cost reference-bandwidth",
02535        NO_STR
02536        "Calculate OSPF interface cost according to bandwidth\n"
02537        "Use reference bandwidth method to assign OSPF cost\n")
02538 {
02539   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
02540   struct listnode *node, *nnode;
02541   struct interface *ifp;
02542 
02543   if (ospf->ref_bandwidth == OSPF_DEFAULT_REF_BANDWIDTH)
02544     return CMD_SUCCESS;
02545   
02546   ospf->ref_bandwidth = OSPF_DEFAULT_REF_BANDWIDTH;
02547   vty_out (vty, "%% OSPF: Reference bandwidth is changed.%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02548   vty_out (vty, "        Please ensure reference bandwidth is consistent across all routers%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02549 
02550   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS (om->iflist, node, nnode, ifp))
02551     ospf_if_recalculate_output_cost (ifp);
02552       
02553   return CMD_SUCCESS;
02554 }

02573 
02574 static void
02575 show_ip_ospf_area (struct vty *vty, struct ospf_area *area)
02576 {
02577   /* Show Area ID. */
02578   vty_out (vty, " Area ID: %s", inet_ntoa (area->area_id));
02579 
02580   /* Show Area type/mode. */
02581   if (OSPF_IS_AREA_BACKBONE (area))
02582     vty_out (vty, " (Backbone)%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02583   else
02584     {
02585       if (area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_STUB)
02586         vty_out (vty, " (Stub%s%s)",
02587                  area->no_summary ? ", no summary" : "",
02588                  area->shortcut_configured ? "; " : "");
02589 
02590       else if (area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_NSSA)
02591         vty_out (vty, " (NSSA%s%s)",
02592                  area->no_summary ? ", no summary" : "",
02593                  area->shortcut_configured ? "; " : "");
02594 
02595       vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02596       vty_out (vty, "   Shortcutting mode: %s",
02597                ospf_shortcut_mode_descr_str[area->shortcut_configured]);
02598       vty_out (vty, ", S-bit consensus: %s%s",
02599                area->shortcut_capability ? "ok" : "no", VTY_NEWLINE);
02600     }
02601 
02602   /* Show number of interfaces. */
02603   vty_out (vty, "   Number of interfaces in this area: Total: %d, "
02604        "Active: %d%s", listcount (area->oiflist),
02605        area->act_ints, VTY_NEWLINE);
02606 
02607   if (area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_NSSA)
02608     {
02609       vty_out (vty, "   It is an NSSA configuration. %s   Elected NSSA/ABR performs type-7/type-5 LSA translation. %s", VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
02610       if (! IS_OSPF_ABR (area->ospf))
02611         vty_out (vty, "   It is not ABR, therefore not Translator. %s",
02612                  VTY_NEWLINE);
02613       else if (area->NSSATranslatorState)
02614        {
02615          vty_out (vty, "   We are an ABR and ");
02616          if (area->NSSATranslatorRole == OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_CANDIDATE)
02617            vty_out (vty, "the NSSA Elected Translator. %s", 
02618                     VTY_NEWLINE);
02619          else if (area->NSSATranslatorRole == OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_ALWAYS)
02620            vty_out (vty, "always an NSSA Translator. %s",
02621                     VTY_NEWLINE);
02622        }
02623       else
02624        {
02625          vty_out (vty, "   We are an ABR, but ");
02626          if (area->NSSATranslatorRole == OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_CANDIDATE)
02627            vty_out (vty, "not the NSSA Elected Translator. %s",
02628                     VTY_NEWLINE);
02629          else
02630            vty_out (vty, "never an NSSA Translator. %s", 
02631                  VTY_NEWLINE);
02632        }
02633     }
02634   /* Stub-router state for this area */
02635   if (CHECK_FLAG (area->stub_router_state, OSPF_AREA_IS_STUB_ROUTED))
02636     {
02637       char timebuf[OSPF_TIME_DUMP_SIZE];
02638       vty_out (vty, "   Originating stub / maximum-distance Router-LSA%s",
02639                VTY_NEWLINE);
02640       if (CHECK_FLAG(area->stub_router_state, OSPF_AREA_ADMIN_STUB_ROUTED))
02641         vty_out (vty, "     Administratively activated (indefinitely)%s",
02642                  VTY_NEWLINE);
02643       if (area->t_stub_router)
02644         vty_out (vty, "     Active from startup, %s remaining%s",
02645                  ospf_timer_dump (area->t_stub_router, timebuf, 
02646                                   sizeof(timebuf)), VTY_NEWLINE);
02647     }
02648   
02649   /* Show number of fully adjacent neighbors. */
02650   vty_out (vty, "   Number of fully adjacent neighbors in this area:"
02651                 " %d%s", area->full_nbrs, VTY_NEWLINE);
02652 
02653   /* Show authentication type. */
02654   vty_out (vty, "   Area has ");
02655   if (area->auth_type == OSPF_AUTH_NULL)
02656     vty_out (vty, "no authentication%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02657   else if (area->auth_type == OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE)
02658     vty_out (vty, "simple password authentication%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02659   else if (area->auth_type == OSPF_AUTH_CRYPTOGRAPHIC)
02660     vty_out (vty, "message digest authentication%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02661 
02662   if (!OSPF_IS_AREA_BACKBONE (area))
02663     vty_out (vty, "   Number of full virtual adjacencies going through"
02664          " this area: %d%s", area->full_vls, VTY_NEWLINE);
02665 
02666   /* Show SPF calculation times. */
02667   vty_out (vty, "   SPF algorithm executed %d times%s",
02668        area->spf_calculation, VTY_NEWLINE);
02669 
02670   /* Show number of LSA. */
02671   vty_out (vty, "   Number of LSA %ld%s", area->lsdb->total, VTY_NEWLINE);
02672   vty_out (vty, "   Number of router LSA %ld. Checksum Sum 0x%08x%s",
02673        ospf_lsdb_count (area->lsdb, OSPF_ROUTER_LSA),
02674        ospf_lsdb_checksum (area->lsdb, OSPF_ROUTER_LSA), VTY_NEWLINE);
02675   vty_out (vty, "   Number of network LSA %ld. Checksum Sum 0x%08x%s",
02676            ospf_lsdb_count (area->lsdb, OSPF_NETWORK_LSA),
02677            ospf_lsdb_checksum (area->lsdb, OSPF_NETWORK_LSA), VTY_NEWLINE);
02678   vty_out (vty, "   Number of summary LSA %ld. Checksum Sum 0x%08x%s",
02679            ospf_lsdb_count (area->lsdb, OSPF_SUMMARY_LSA),
02680            ospf_lsdb_checksum (area->lsdb, OSPF_SUMMARY_LSA), VTY_NEWLINE);
02681   vty_out (vty, "   Number of ASBR summary LSA %ld. Checksum Sum 0x%08x%s",
02682            ospf_lsdb_count (area->lsdb, OSPF_ASBR_SUMMARY_LSA),
02683            ospf_lsdb_checksum (area->lsdb, OSPF_ASBR_SUMMARY_LSA), VTY_NEWLINE);
02684   vty_out (vty, "   Number of NSSA LSA %ld. Checksum Sum 0x%08x%s",
02685            ospf_lsdb_count (area->lsdb, OSPF_AS_NSSA_LSA),
02686            ospf_lsdb_checksum (area->lsdb, OSPF_AS_NSSA_LSA), VTY_NEWLINE);
02687 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
02688   vty_out (vty, "   Number of opaque link LSA %ld. Checksum Sum 0x%08x%s",
02689            ospf_lsdb_count (area->lsdb, OSPF_OPAQUE_LINK_LSA),
02690            ospf_lsdb_checksum (area->lsdb, OSPF_OPAQUE_LINK_LSA), VTY_NEWLINE);
02691   vty_out (vty, "   Number of opaque area LSA %ld. Checksum Sum 0x%08x%s",
02692            ospf_lsdb_count (area->lsdb, OSPF_OPAQUE_AREA_LSA),
02693            ospf_lsdb_checksum (area->lsdb, OSPF_OPAQUE_AREA_LSA), VTY_NEWLINE);
02694 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
02695   vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02696 }
02697 
02698 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf,
02699        show_ip_ospf_cmd,
02700        "show ip ospf",
02701        SHOW_STR
02702        IP_STR
02703        "OSPF information\n")
02704 {
02705   struct listnode *node, *nnode;
02706   struct ospf_area * area;
02707   struct ospf *ospf;
02708   struct timeval result;
02709   char timebuf[OSPF_TIME_DUMP_SIZE];
02710 
02711   /* Check OSPF is enable. */
02712   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
02713   if (ospf == NULL)
02714     {
02715       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02716       return CMD_SUCCESS;
02717     }
02718 
02719   /* Show Router ID. */
02720   vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process, Router ID: %s%s",
02721            inet_ntoa (ospf->router_id),
02722            VTY_NEWLINE);
02723   
02724   /* Graceful shutdown */
02725   if (ospf->t_deferred_shutdown)
02726     vty_out (vty, " Deferred shutdown in progress, %s remaining%s",
02727              ospf_timer_dump (ospf->t_deferred_shutdown,
02728                               timebuf, sizeof (timebuf)), VTY_NEWLINE);
02729   /* Show capability. */
02730   vty_out (vty, " Supports only single TOS (TOS0) routes%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02731   vty_out (vty, " This implementation conforms to RFC2328%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02732   vty_out (vty, " RFC1583Compatibility flag is %s%s",
02733        CHECK_FLAG (ospf->config, OSPF_RFC1583_COMPATIBLE) ?
02734        "enabled" : "disabled", VTY_NEWLINE);
02735 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
02736   vty_out (vty, " OpaqueCapability flag is %s%s%s",
02737        CHECK_FLAG (ospf->config, OSPF_OPAQUE_CAPABLE) ?
02738            "enabled" : "disabled",
02739            IS_OPAQUE_LSA_ORIGINATION_BLOCKED (ospf->opaque) ?
02740            " (origination blocked)" : "",
02741            VTY_NEWLINE);
02742 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
02743   
02744   /* Show stub-router configuration */
02745   if (ospf->stub_router_startup_time != OSPF_STUB_ROUTER_UNCONFIGURED
02746       || ospf->stub_router_shutdown_time != OSPF_STUB_ROUTER_UNCONFIGURED)
02747     {
02748       vty_out (vty, " Stub router advertisement is configured%s",
02749                VTY_NEWLINE);
02750       if (ospf->stub_router_startup_time != OSPF_STUB_ROUTER_UNCONFIGURED)
02751         vty_out (vty, "   Enabled for %us after start-up%s",
02752                  ospf->stub_router_startup_time, VTY_NEWLINE);
02753       if (ospf->stub_router_shutdown_time != OSPF_STUB_ROUTER_UNCONFIGURED)
02754         vty_out (vty, "   Enabled for %us prior to full shutdown%s",
02755                  ospf->stub_router_shutdown_time, VTY_NEWLINE);
02756     }
02757   
02758   /* Show SPF timers. */
02759   vty_out (vty, " Initial SPF scheduling delay %d millisec(s)%s"
02760                 " Minimum hold time between consecutive SPFs %d millisec(s)%s"
02761                 " Maximum hold time between consecutive SPFs %d millisec(s)%s"
02762                 " Hold time multiplier is currently %d%s",
02763       ospf->spf_delay, VTY_NEWLINE,
02764       ospf->spf_holdtime, VTY_NEWLINE,
02765       ospf->spf_max_holdtime, VTY_NEWLINE,
02766       ospf->spf_hold_multiplier, VTY_NEWLINE);
02767   vty_out (vty, " SPF algorithm ");
02768   if (ospf->ts_spf.tv_sec || ospf->ts_spf.tv_usec)
02769     {
02770       result = tv_sub (recent_relative_time (), ospf->ts_spf);
02771       vty_out (vty, "last executed %s ago%s",
02772                ospf_timeval_dump (&result, timebuf, sizeof (timebuf)),
02773                VTY_NEWLINE);
02774     }
02775   else
02776     vty_out (vty, "has not been run%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02777   vty_out (vty, " SPF timer %s%s%s",
02778            (ospf->t_spf_calc ? "due in " : "is "),
02779            ospf_timer_dump (ospf->t_spf_calc, timebuf, sizeof (timebuf)),
02780            VTY_NEWLINE);
02781   
02782   /* Show refresh parameters. */
02783   vty_out (vty, " Refresh timer %d secs%s",
02784        ospf->lsa_refresh_interval, VTY_NEWLINE);
02785        
02786   /* Show ABR/ASBR flags. */
02787   if (CHECK_FLAG (ospf->flags, OSPF_FLAG_ABR))
02788     vty_out (vty, " This router is an ABR, ABR type is: %s%s",
02789              ospf_abr_type_descr_str[ospf->abr_type], VTY_NEWLINE);
02790 
02791   if (CHECK_FLAG (ospf->flags, OSPF_FLAG_ASBR))
02792     vty_out (vty, " This router is an ASBR "
02793              "(injecting external routing information)%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02794 
02795   /* Show Number of AS-external-LSAs. */
02796   vty_out (vty, " Number of external LSA %ld. Checksum Sum 0x%08x%s",
02797        ospf_lsdb_count (ospf->lsdb, OSPF_AS_EXTERNAL_LSA),
02798        ospf_lsdb_checksum (ospf->lsdb, OSPF_AS_EXTERNAL_LSA), VTY_NEWLINE);
02799 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
02800   vty_out (vty, " Number of opaque AS LSA %ld. Checksum Sum 0x%08x%s",
02801        ospf_lsdb_count (ospf->lsdb, OSPF_OPAQUE_AS_LSA),
02802        ospf_lsdb_checksum (ospf->lsdb, OSPF_OPAQUE_AS_LSA), VTY_NEWLINE);
02803 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
02804   /* Show number of areas attached. */
02805   vty_out (vty, " Number of areas attached to this router: %d%s",
02806            listcount (ospf->areas), VTY_NEWLINE);
02807 
02808   if (CHECK_FLAG(ospf->config, OSPF_LOG_ADJACENCY_CHANGES))
02809     {
02810       if (CHECK_FLAG(ospf->config, OSPF_LOG_ADJACENCY_DETAIL))
02811     vty_out(vty, " All adjacency changes are logged%s",VTY_NEWLINE);
02812       else
02813     vty_out(vty, " Adjacency changes are logged%s",VTY_NEWLINE);
02814     }
02815 
02816   vty_out (vty, "%s",VTY_NEWLINE);
02817 
02818   /* Show each area status. */
02819   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS (ospf->areas, node, nnode, area))
02820     show_ip_ospf_area (vty, area);
02821 
02822   return CMD_SUCCESS;
02823 }
02824 
02825 
02826 static void
02827 show_ip_ospf_interface_sub (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf,
02828                 struct interface *ifp)
02829 {
02830   int is_up;
02831   struct ospf_neighbor *nbr;
02832   struct route_node *rn;
02833 
02834   /* Is interface up? */
02835   vty_out (vty, "%s is %s%s", ifp->name,
02836        ((is_up = if_is_operative(ifp)) ? "up" : "down"), VTY_NEWLINE);
02837   vty_out (vty, "  ifindex %u, MTU %u bytes, BW %u Kbit %s%s",
02838        ifp->ifindex, ifp->mtu, ifp->bandwidth, if_flag_dump(ifp->flags),
02839        VTY_NEWLINE);
02840 
02841   /* Is interface OSPF enabled? */
02842   if (ospf_oi_count(ifp) == 0)
02843     {
02844       vty_out (vty, "  OSPF not enabled on this interface%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02845       return;
02846     }
02847   else if (!is_up)
02848     {
02849       vty_out (vty, "  OSPF is enabled, but not running on this interface%s",
02850            VTY_NEWLINE);
02851       return;
02852     }
02853 
02854   for (rn = route_top (IF_OIFS (ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
02855     {
02856       struct ospf_interface *oi = rn->info;
02857       
02858       if (oi == NULL)
02859     continue;
02860       
02861       /* Show OSPF interface information. */
02862       vty_out (vty, "  Internet Address %s/%d,",
02863            inet_ntoa (oi->address->u.prefix4), oi->address->prefixlen);
02864 
02865       if (oi->connected->destination || oi->type == OSPF_IFTYPE_VIRTUALLINK)
02866         {
02867           struct in_addr *dest;
02868           const char *dstr;
02869           
02870       if (CONNECTED_PEER(oi->connected)
02871           || oi->type == OSPF_IFTYPE_VIRTUALLINK)
02872             dstr = "Peer";
02873           else
02874             dstr = "Broadcast";
02875           
02876           /* For Vlinks, showing the peer address is probably more
02877            * informative than the local interface that is being used
02878            */
02879           if (oi->type == OSPF_IFTYPE_VIRTUALLINK)
02880             dest = &oi->vl_data->peer_addr;
02881           else
02882             dest = &oi->connected->destination->u.prefix4;
02883           
02884       vty_out (vty, " %s %s,", dstr, inet_ntoa (*dest));
02885         }
02886 
02887       vty_out (vty, " Area %s%s", ospf_area_desc_string (oi->area),
02888            VTY_NEWLINE);
02889 
02890       vty_out (vty, "  MTU mismatch detection:%s%s",
02891            OSPF_IF_PARAM(oi, mtu_ignore) ? "disabled" : "enabled", VTY_NEWLINE);
02892 
02893       vty_out (vty, "  Router ID %s, Network Type %s, Cost: %d%s",
02894            inet_ntoa (ospf->router_id), ospf_network_type_str[oi->type],
02895            oi->output_cost, VTY_NEWLINE);
02896 
02897       vty_out (vty, "  Transmit Delay is %d sec, State %s, Priority %d%s",
02898            OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi,transmit_delay), LOOKUP (ospf_ism_state_msg, oi->state),
02899            PRIORITY (oi), VTY_NEWLINE);
02900 
02901   /* Show DR information. */
02902       if (DR (oi).s_addr == 0)
02903     vty_out (vty, "  No designated router on this network%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02904       else
02905     {
02906       nbr = ospf_nbr_lookup_by_addr (oi->nbrs, &DR (oi));
02907       if (nbr == NULL)
02908         vty_out (vty, "  No designated router on this network%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02909       else
02910         {
02911           vty_out (vty, "  Designated Router (ID) %s,",
02912                inet_ntoa (nbr->router_id));
02913           vty_out (vty, " Interface Address %s%s",
02914                inet_ntoa (nbr->address.u.prefix4), VTY_NEWLINE);
02915         }
02916     }
02917 
02918       /* Show BDR information. */
02919       if (BDR (oi).s_addr == 0)
02920     vty_out (vty, "  No backup designated router on this network%s",
02921          VTY_NEWLINE);
02922       else
02923     {
02924       nbr = ospf_nbr_lookup_by_addr (oi->nbrs, &BDR (oi));
02925       if (nbr == NULL)
02926         vty_out (vty, "  No backup designated router on this network%s",
02927              VTY_NEWLINE);
02928       else
02929         {
02930           vty_out (vty, "  Backup Designated Router (ID) %s,",
02931                inet_ntoa (nbr->router_id));
02932           vty_out (vty, " Interface Address %s%s",
02933                inet_ntoa (nbr->address.u.prefix4), VTY_NEWLINE);
02934         }
02935     }
02936 
02937       vty_out (vty, "  Multicast group memberships:");
02938       if (OI_MEMBER_CHECK(oi, MEMBER_ALLROUTERS)
02939           || OI_MEMBER_CHECK(oi, MEMBER_DROUTERS))
02940         {
02941           if (OI_MEMBER_CHECK(oi, MEMBER_ALLROUTERS))
02942             vty_out (vty, " OSPFAllRouters");
02943           if (OI_MEMBER_CHECK(oi, MEMBER_DROUTERS))
02944             vty_out (vty, " OSPFDesignatedRouters");
02945         }
02946       else
02947         vty_out (vty, " <None>");
02948       vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02949 
02950       vty_out (vty, "  Timer intervals configured,");
02951       vty_out (vty, " Hello ");
02952       if (OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, fast_hello) == 0)
02953         vty_out (vty, "%ds,", OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, v_hello));
02954       else
02955         vty_out (vty, "%dms,", 1000 / OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, fast_hello));
02956       vty_out (vty, " Dead %ds, Wait %ds, Retransmit %d%s",
02957            OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, v_wait),
02958            OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, v_wait),
02959            OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, retransmit_interval),
02960            VTY_NEWLINE);
02961       
02962       if (OSPF_IF_PASSIVE_STATUS (oi) == OSPF_IF_ACTIVE)
02963         {
02964       char timebuf[OSPF_TIME_DUMP_SIZE];
02965       vty_out (vty, "    Hello due in %s%s",
02966            ospf_timer_dump (oi->t_hello, timebuf, sizeof(timebuf)), 
02967            VTY_NEWLINE);
02968         }
02969       else /* passive-interface is set */
02970     vty_out (vty, "    No Hellos (Passive interface)%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02971       
02972       vty_out (vty, "  Neighbor Count is %d, Adjacent neighbor count is %d%s",
02973            ospf_nbr_count (oi, 0), ospf_nbr_count (oi, NSM_Full),
02974            VTY_NEWLINE);
02975     }
02976 }
02977 
02978 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_interface,
02979        show_ip_ospf_interface_cmd,
02980        "show ip ospf interface [INTERFACE]",
02981        SHOW_STR
02982        IP_STR
02983        "OSPF information\n"
02984        "Interface information\n"
02985        "Interface name\n")
02986 {
02987   struct interface *ifp;
02988   struct ospf *ospf;
02989   struct listnode *node;
02990 
02991   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
02992   if (ospf == NULL)
02993     {
02994       vty_out (vty, "OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
02995       return CMD_SUCCESS;
02996     }
02997 
02998   /* Show All Interfaces. */
02999   if (argc == 0)
03000     for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (iflist, node, ifp))
03001       show_ip_ospf_interface_sub (vty, ospf, ifp);
03002   /* Interface name is specified. */
03003   else
03004     {
03005       if ((ifp = if_lookup_by_name (argv[0])) == NULL)
03006         vty_out (vty, "No such interface name%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03007       else
03008         show_ip_ospf_interface_sub (vty, ospf, ifp);
03009     }
03010 
03011   return CMD_SUCCESS;
03012 }
03013 
03014 static void
03015 show_ip_ospf_neighbour_header (struct vty *vty)
03016 {
03017   vty_out (vty, "%s%15s %3s %-15s %9s %-15s %-20s %5s %5s %5s%s",
03018            VTY_NEWLINE,
03019            "Neighbor ID", "Pri", "State", "Dead Time",
03020            "Address", "Interface", "RXmtL", "RqstL", "DBsmL",
03021            VTY_NEWLINE);
03022 }
03023 
03024 static void
03025 show_ip_ospf_neighbor_sub (struct vty *vty, struct ospf_interface *oi)
03026 {
03027   struct route_node *rn;
03028   struct ospf_neighbor *nbr;
03029   char msgbuf[16];
03030   char timebuf[OSPF_TIME_DUMP_SIZE];
03031 
03032   for (rn = route_top (oi->nbrs); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
03033     if ((nbr = rn->info))
03034       /* Do not show myself. */
03035       if (nbr != oi->nbr_self)
03036     /* Down state is not shown. */
03037     if (nbr->state != NSM_Down)
03038       {
03039         ospf_nbr_state_message (nbr, msgbuf, 16);
03040 
03041         if (nbr->state == NSM_Attempt && nbr->router_id.s_addr == 0)
03042           vty_out (vty, "%-15s %3d %-15s ",
03043                "-", nbr->priority,
03044                msgbuf);
03045             else
03046           vty_out (vty, "%-15s %3d %-15s ",
03047                inet_ntoa (nbr->router_id), nbr->priority,
03048                msgbuf);
03049             
03050             vty_out (vty, "%9s ",
03051                      ospf_timer_dump (nbr->t_inactivity, timebuf, 
03052                                       sizeof(timebuf)));
03053             
03054         vty_out (vty, "%-15s ", inet_ntoa (nbr->src));
03055         vty_out (vty, "%-20s %5ld %5ld %5d%s",
03056              IF_NAME (oi), ospf_ls_retransmit_count (nbr),
03057              ospf_ls_request_count (nbr), ospf_db_summary_count (nbr),
03058              VTY_NEWLINE);
03059       }
03060 }
03061 
03062 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_neighbor,
03063        show_ip_ospf_neighbor_cmd,
03064        "show ip ospf neighbor",
03065        SHOW_STR
03066        IP_STR
03067        "OSPF information\n"
03068        "Neighbor list\n")
03069 {
03070   struct ospf *ospf;
03071   struct ospf_interface *oi;
03072   struct listnode *node;
03073 
03074   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
03075   if (ospf == NULL)
03076     {
03077       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03078       return CMD_SUCCESS;
03079     }
03080 
03081   show_ip_ospf_neighbour_header (vty);
03082 
03083   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->oiflist, node, oi))
03084     show_ip_ospf_neighbor_sub (vty, oi);
03085 
03086   return CMD_SUCCESS;
03087 }
03088 
03089 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_neighbor_all,
03090        show_ip_ospf_neighbor_all_cmd,
03091        "show ip ospf neighbor all",
03092        SHOW_STR
03093        IP_STR
03094        "OSPF information\n"
03095        "Neighbor list\n"
03096        "include down status neighbor\n")
03097 {
03098   struct ospf *ospf = ospf_lookup ();
03099   struct listnode *node;
03100   struct ospf_interface *oi;
03101 
03102   if (ospf == NULL)
03103     {
03104       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03105       return CMD_SUCCESS;
03106     }
03107   
03108   show_ip_ospf_neighbour_header (vty);
03109   
03110   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->oiflist, node, oi))
03111     {
03112       struct listnode *nbr_node;
03113       struct ospf_nbr_nbma *nbr_nbma;
03114 
03115       show_ip_ospf_neighbor_sub (vty, oi);
03116 
03117     /* print Down neighbor status */
03118     for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (oi->nbr_nbma, nbr_node, nbr_nbma))
03119       {
03120     if (nbr_nbma->nbr == NULL
03121         || nbr_nbma->nbr->state == NSM_Down)
03122       {
03123         vty_out (vty, "%-15s %3d %-15s %9s ",
03124              "-", nbr_nbma->priority, "Down", "-");
03125         vty_out (vty, "%-15s %-20s %5d %5d %5d%s", 
03126              inet_ntoa (nbr_nbma->addr), IF_NAME (oi),
03127              0, 0, 0, VTY_NEWLINE);
03128       }
03129       }
03130     }
03131 
03132   return CMD_SUCCESS;
03133 }

03135 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_neighbor_int,
03136        show_ip_ospf_neighbor_int_cmd,
03137        "show ip ospf neighbor IFNAME",
03138        SHOW_STR
03139        IP_STR
03140        "OSPF information\n"
03141        "Neighbor list\n"
03142        "Interface name\n")
03143 {
03144   struct ospf *ospf;
03145   struct interface *ifp;
03146   struct route_node *rn;
03147  
03148   ifp = if_lookup_by_name (argv[0]);
03149   if (!ifp)
03150     {
03151       vty_out (vty, "No such interface.%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03152       return CMD_WARNING;
03153     }
03154 
03155   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
03156   if (ospf == NULL)
03157     {
03158       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03159       return CMD_SUCCESS;
03160     }
03161   
03162   show_ip_ospf_neighbour_header (vty);
03163   
03164   for (rn = route_top (IF_OIFS (ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
03165     {
03166       struct ospf_interface *oi = rn->info;
03167 
03168       if (oi == NULL)
03169     continue;
03170 
03171       show_ip_ospf_neighbor_sub (vty, oi);
03172     }
03173 
03174   return CMD_SUCCESS;
03175 }

03177 static void
03178 show_ip_ospf_nbr_nbma_detail_sub (struct vty *vty, struct ospf_interface *oi,
03179                   struct ospf_nbr_nbma *nbr_nbma)
03180 {
03181   char timebuf[OSPF_TIME_DUMP_SIZE];
03182 
03183   /* Show neighbor ID. */
03184   vty_out (vty, " Neighbor %s,", "-");
03185 
03186   /* Show interface address. */
03187   vty_out (vty, " interface address %s%s",
03188        inet_ntoa (nbr_nbma->addr), VTY_NEWLINE);
03189   /* Show Area ID. */
03190   vty_out (vty, "    In the area %s via interface %s%s",
03191        ospf_area_desc_string (oi->area), IF_NAME (oi), VTY_NEWLINE);
03192   /* Show neighbor priority and state. */
03193   vty_out (vty, "    Neighbor priority is %d, State is %s,",
03194        nbr_nbma->priority, "Down");
03195   /* Show state changes. */
03196   vty_out (vty, " %d state changes%s", nbr_nbma->state_change, VTY_NEWLINE);
03197 
03198   /* Show PollInterval */
03199   vty_out (vty, "    Poll interval %d%s", nbr_nbma->v_poll, VTY_NEWLINE);
03200 
03201   /* Show poll-interval timer. */
03202   vty_out (vty, "    Poll timer due in %s%s",
03203        ospf_timer_dump (nbr_nbma->t_poll, timebuf, sizeof(timebuf)),
03204            VTY_NEWLINE);
03205 
03206   /* Show poll-interval timer thread. */
03207   vty_out (vty, "    Thread Poll Timer %s%s", 
03208        nbr_nbma->t_poll != NULL ? "on" : "off", VTY_NEWLINE);
03209 }
03210 
03211 static void
03212 show_ip_ospf_neighbor_detail_sub (struct vty *vty, struct ospf_interface *oi,
03213                   struct ospf_neighbor *nbr)
03214 {
03215   char timebuf[OSPF_TIME_DUMP_SIZE];
03216 
03217   /* Show neighbor ID. */
03218   if (nbr->state == NSM_Attempt && nbr->router_id.s_addr == 0)
03219     vty_out (vty, " Neighbor %s,", "-");
03220   else
03221   vty_out (vty, " Neighbor %s,", inet_ntoa (nbr->router_id));
03222 
03223   /* Show interface address. */
03224   vty_out (vty, " interface address %s%s",
03225        inet_ntoa (nbr->address.u.prefix4), VTY_NEWLINE);
03226   /* Show Area ID. */
03227   vty_out (vty, "    In the area %s via interface %s%s",
03228        ospf_area_desc_string (oi->area), oi->ifp->name, VTY_NEWLINE);
03229   /* Show neighbor priority and state. */
03230   vty_out (vty, "    Neighbor priority is %d, State is %s,",
03231        nbr->priority, LOOKUP (ospf_nsm_state_msg, nbr->state));
03232   /* Show state changes. */
03233   vty_out (vty, " %d state changes%s", nbr->state_change, VTY_NEWLINE);
03234   if (nbr->ts_last_progress.tv_sec || nbr->ts_last_progress.tv_usec)
03235     {
03236       struct timeval res
03237         = tv_sub (recent_relative_time (), nbr->ts_last_progress);
03238       vty_out (vty, "    Most recent state change statistics:%s",
03239                VTY_NEWLINE);
03240       vty_out (vty, "      Progressive change %s ago%s",
03241                ospf_timeval_dump (&res, timebuf, sizeof(timebuf)),
03242                VTY_NEWLINE);
03243     }
03244   if (nbr->ts_last_regress.tv_sec || nbr->ts_last_regress.tv_usec)
03245     {
03246       struct timeval res
03247         = tv_sub (recent_relative_time (), nbr->ts_last_regress);
03248       vty_out (vty, "      Regressive change %s ago, due to %s%s",
03249                ospf_timeval_dump (&res, timebuf, sizeof(timebuf)),
03250                (nbr->last_regress_str ? nbr->last_regress_str : "??"),
03251                VTY_NEWLINE);
03252     }
03253   /* Show Designated Rotuer ID. */
03254   vty_out (vty, "    DR is %s,", inet_ntoa (nbr->d_router));
03255   /* Show Backup Designated Rotuer ID. */
03256   vty_out (vty, " BDR is %s%s", inet_ntoa (nbr->bd_router), VTY_NEWLINE);
03257   /* Show options. */
03258   vty_out (vty, "    Options %d %s%s", nbr->options,
03259        ospf_options_dump (nbr->options), VTY_NEWLINE);
03260   /* Show Router Dead interval timer. */
03261   vty_out (vty, "    Dead timer due in %s%s",
03262        ospf_timer_dump (nbr->t_inactivity, timebuf, sizeof (timebuf)),
03263            VTY_NEWLINE);
03264   /* Show Database Summary list. */
03265   vty_out (vty, "    Database Summary List %d%s",
03266        ospf_db_summary_count (nbr), VTY_NEWLINE);
03267   /* Show Link State Request list. */
03268   vty_out (vty, "    Link State Request List %ld%s",
03269        ospf_ls_request_count (nbr), VTY_NEWLINE);
03270   /* Show Link State Retransmission list. */
03271   vty_out (vty, "    Link State Retransmission List %ld%s",
03272        ospf_ls_retransmit_count (nbr), VTY_NEWLINE);
03273   /* Show inactivity timer thread. */
03274   vty_out (vty, "    Thread Inactivity Timer %s%s", 
03275        nbr->t_inactivity != NULL ? "on" : "off", VTY_NEWLINE);
03276   /* Show Database Description retransmission thread. */
03277   vty_out (vty, "    Thread Database Description Retransmision %s%s",
03278        nbr->t_db_desc != NULL ? "on" : "off", VTY_NEWLINE);
03279   /* Show Link State Request Retransmission thread. */
03280   vty_out (vty, "    Thread Link State Request Retransmission %s%s",
03281        nbr->t_ls_req != NULL ? "on" : "off", VTY_NEWLINE);
03282   /* Show Link State Update Retransmission thread. */
03283   vty_out (vty, "    Thread Link State Update Retransmission %s%s%s",
03284        nbr->t_ls_upd != NULL ? "on" : "off", VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
03285 }
03286 
03287 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_neighbor_id,
03288        show_ip_ospf_neighbor_id_cmd,
03289        "show ip ospf neighbor A.B.C.D",
03290        SHOW_STR
03291        IP_STR
03292        "OSPF information\n"
03293        "Neighbor list\n"
03294        "Neighbor ID\n")
03295 {
03296   struct ospf *ospf;
03297   struct listnode *node;
03298   struct ospf_neighbor *nbr;
03299   struct ospf_interface *oi;
03300   struct in_addr router_id;
03301   int ret;
03302 
03303   ret = inet_aton (argv[0], &router_id);
03304   if (!ret)
03305     {
03306       vty_out (vty, "Please specify Neighbor ID by A.B.C.D%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03307       return CMD_WARNING;
03308     }
03309 
03310   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
03311   if (ospf == NULL)
03312     {
03313       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03314       return CMD_SUCCESS;
03315     }
03316 
03317   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->oiflist, node, oi))
03318     if ((nbr = ospf_nbr_lookup_by_routerid (oi->nbrs, &router_id)))
03319       show_ip_ospf_neighbor_detail_sub (vty, oi, nbr);
03320 
03321   return CMD_SUCCESS;
03322 }

03324 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_neighbor_detail,
03325        show_ip_ospf_neighbor_detail_cmd,
03326        "show ip ospf neighbor detail",
03327        SHOW_STR
03328        IP_STR
03329        "OSPF information\n"
03330        "Neighbor list\n"
03331        "detail of all neighbors\n")
03332 {
03333   struct ospf *ospf;
03334   struct ospf_interface *oi;
03335   struct listnode *node;
03336 
03337   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
03338   if (ospf == NULL)
03339     {
03340       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03341       return CMD_SUCCESS;
03342     }
03343 
03344   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->oiflist, node, oi))
03345     {
03346       struct route_node *rn;
03347       struct ospf_neighbor *nbr;
03348 
03349       for (rn = route_top (oi->nbrs); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
03350     if ((nbr = rn->info))
03351       if (nbr != oi->nbr_self)
03352         if (nbr->state != NSM_Down)
03353           show_ip_ospf_neighbor_detail_sub (vty, oi, nbr);
03354     }
03355 
03356   return CMD_SUCCESS;
03357 }
