03359 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_neighbor_detail_all,
03360        show_ip_ospf_neighbor_detail_all_cmd,
03361        "show ip ospf neighbor detail all",
03362        SHOW_STR
03363        IP_STR
03364        "OSPF information\n"
03365        "Neighbor list\n"
03366        "detail of all neighbors\n"
03367        "include down status neighbor\n")
03368 {
03369   struct ospf *ospf;
03370   struct listnode *node;
03371   struct ospf_interface *oi;
03372 
03373   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
03374   if (ospf == NULL)
03375     {
03376       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03377       return CMD_SUCCESS;
03378     }
03379 
03380   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->oiflist, node, oi))
03381     {
03382       struct route_node *rn;
03383       struct ospf_neighbor *nbr;
03384       struct ospf_nbr_nbma *nbr_nbma;
03385 
03386       for (rn = route_top (oi->nbrs); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
03387     if ((nbr = rn->info))
03388       if (nbr != oi->nbr_self)
03389         if (oi->type == OSPF_IFTYPE_NBMA && nbr->state != NSM_Down)
03390           show_ip_ospf_neighbor_detail_sub (vty, oi, rn->info);
03391 
03392       if (oi->type == OSPF_IFTYPE_NBMA)
03393     {
03394       struct listnode *nd;
03395 
03396       for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (oi->nbr_nbma, nd, nbr_nbma))
03397             if (nbr_nbma->nbr == NULL
03398                 || nbr_nbma->nbr->state == NSM_Down)
03399               show_ip_ospf_nbr_nbma_detail_sub (vty, oi, nbr_nbma);
03400     }
03401     }
03402 
03403   return CMD_SUCCESS;
03404 }
03405 
03406 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_neighbor_int_detail,
03407        show_ip_ospf_neighbor_int_detail_cmd,
03408        "show ip ospf neighbor IFNAME detail",
03409        SHOW_STR
03410        IP_STR
03411        "OSPF information\n"
03412        "Neighbor list\n"
03413        "Interface name\n"
03414        "detail of all neighbors")
03415 {
03416   struct ospf *ospf;
03417   struct ospf_interface *oi;
03418   struct interface *ifp;
03419   struct route_node *rn, *nrn;
03420   struct ospf_neighbor *nbr;
03421 
03422   ifp = if_lookup_by_name (argv[0]);
03423   if (!ifp)
03424     {
03425       vty_out (vty, "No such interface.%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03426       return CMD_WARNING;
03427     }
03428 
03429   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
03430   if (ospf == NULL)
03431     {
03432       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03433       return CMD_SUCCESS;
03434     }
03435 
03436 
03437   for (rn = route_top (IF_OIFS (ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
03438     if ((oi = rn->info))
03439       for (nrn = route_top (oi->nbrs); nrn; nrn = route_next (nrn))
03440     if ((nbr = nrn->info))
03441       if (nbr != oi->nbr_self)
03442         if (nbr->state != NSM_Down)
03443           show_ip_ospf_neighbor_detail_sub (vty, oi, nbr);
03444 
03445   return CMD_SUCCESS;
03446 }
03447 
03448 
03449 /* Show functions */
03450 static int
03451 show_lsa_summary (struct vty *vty, struct ospf_lsa *lsa, int self)
03452 {
03453   struct router_lsa *rl;
03454   struct summary_lsa *sl;
03455   struct as_external_lsa *asel;
03456   struct prefix_ipv4 p;
03457 
03458   if (lsa != NULL)
03459     /* If self option is set, check LSA self flag. */
03460     if (self == 0 || IS_LSA_SELF (lsa))
03461       {
03462     /* LSA common part show. */
03463     vty_out (vty, "%-15s ", inet_ntoa (lsa->data->id));
03464     vty_out (vty, "%-15s %4d 0x%08lx 0x%04x",
03465          inet_ntoa (lsa->data->adv_router), LS_AGE (lsa),
03466          (u_long)ntohl (lsa->data->ls_seqnum), ntohs (lsa->data->checksum));
03467     /* LSA specific part show. */
03468     switch (lsa->data->type)
03469       {
03470       case OSPF_ROUTER_LSA:
03471         rl = (struct router_lsa *) lsa->data;
03472         vty_out (vty, " %-d", ntohs (rl->links));
03473         break;
03474       case OSPF_SUMMARY_LSA:
03475         sl = (struct summary_lsa *) lsa->data;
03476 
03477         p.family = AF_INET;
03478         p.prefix = sl->header.id;
03479         p.prefixlen = ip_masklen (sl->mask);
03480         apply_mask_ipv4 (&p);
03481 
03482         vty_out (vty, " %s/%d", inet_ntoa (p.prefix), p.prefixlen);
03483         break;
03484       case OSPF_AS_EXTERNAL_LSA:
03485       case OSPF_AS_NSSA_LSA:
03486         asel = (struct as_external_lsa *) lsa->data;
03487 
03488         p.family = AF_INET;
03489         p.prefix = asel->header.id;
03490         p.prefixlen = ip_masklen (asel->mask);
03491         apply_mask_ipv4 (&p);
03492 
03493         vty_out (vty, " %s %s/%d [0x%lx]",
03494              IS_EXTERNAL_METRIC (asel->e[0].tos) ? "E2" : "E1",
03495              inet_ntoa (p.prefix), p.prefixlen,
03496              (u_long)ntohl (asel->e[0].route_tag));
03497         break;
03498       case OSPF_NETWORK_LSA:
03499       case OSPF_ASBR_SUMMARY_LSA:
03500 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
03501       case OSPF_OPAQUE_LINK_LSA:
03502       case OSPF_OPAQUE_AREA_LSA:
03503       case OSPF_OPAQUE_AS_LSA:
03504 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
03505       default:
03506         break;
03507       }
03508     vty_out (vty, VTY_NEWLINE);
03509       }
03510 
03511   return 0;
03512 }

03550 static void
03551 show_ip_ospf_database_header (struct vty *vty, struct ospf_lsa *lsa)
03552 {
03553   struct router_lsa *rlsa = (struct router_lsa*) lsa->data;
03554   
03555   vty_out (vty, "  LS age: %d%s", LS_AGE (lsa), VTY_NEWLINE);
03556   vty_out (vty, "  Options: 0x%-2x : %s%s", 
03557            lsa->data->options,
03558            ospf_options_dump(lsa->data->options), 
03559            VTY_NEWLINE);
03560   vty_out (vty, "  LS Flags: 0x%-2x %s%s",
03561            lsa->flags,
03562            ((lsa->flags & OSPF_LSA_LOCAL_XLT) ? "(Translated from Type-7)" : ""),
03563            VTY_NEWLINE);
03564 
03565   if (lsa->data->type == OSPF_ROUTER_LSA)
03566     {
03567       vty_out (vty, "  Flags: 0x%x" , rlsa->flags);
03568 
03569       if (rlsa->flags)
03570     vty_out (vty, " :%s%s%s%s",
03571          IS_ROUTER_LSA_BORDER (rlsa) ? " ABR" : "",
03572          IS_ROUTER_LSA_EXTERNAL (rlsa) ? " ASBR" : "",
03573          IS_ROUTER_LSA_VIRTUAL (rlsa) ? " VL-endpoint" : "",
03574          IS_ROUTER_LSA_SHORTCUT (rlsa) ? " Shortcut" : "");
03575 
03576       vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03577     }
03578   vty_out (vty, "  LS Type: %s%s",
03579            LOOKUP (ospf_lsa_type_msg, lsa->data->type), VTY_NEWLINE);
03580   vty_out (vty, "  Link State ID: %s %s%s", inet_ntoa (lsa->data->id),
03581            LOOKUP (ospf_link_state_id_type_msg, lsa->data->type), VTY_NEWLINE);
03582   vty_out (vty, "  Advertising Router: %s%s",
03583            inet_ntoa (lsa->data->adv_router), VTY_NEWLINE);
03584   vty_out (vty, "  LS Seq Number: %08lx%s", (u_long)ntohl (lsa->data->ls_seqnum),
03585            VTY_NEWLINE);
03586   vty_out (vty, "  Checksum: 0x%04x%s", ntohs (lsa->data->checksum),
03587            VTY_NEWLINE);
03588   vty_out (vty, "  Length: %d%s", ntohs (lsa->data->length), VTY_NEWLINE);
03589 }

03618 /* Show router-LSA each Link information. */
03619 static void
03620 show_ip_ospf_database_router_links (struct vty *vty,
03621                                     struct router_lsa *rl)
03622 {
03623   int len, i, type;
03624 
03625   len = ntohs (rl->header.length) - 4;
03626   for (i = 0; i < ntohs (rl->links) && len > 0; len -= 12, i++)
03627     {
03628       type = rl->link[i].type;
03629 
03630       vty_out (vty, "    Link connected to: %s%s",
03631            link_type_desc[type], VTY_NEWLINE);
03632       vty_out (vty, "     (Link ID) %s: %s%s", link_id_desc[type],
03633            inet_ntoa (rl->link[i].link_id), VTY_NEWLINE);
03634       vty_out (vty, "     (Link Data) %s: %s%s", link_data_desc[type],
03635            inet_ntoa (rl->link[i].link_data), VTY_NEWLINE);
03636       vty_out (vty, "      Number of TOS metrics: 0%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03637       vty_out (vty, "       TOS 0 Metric: %d%s",
03638            ntohs (rl->link[i].metric), VTY_NEWLINE);
03639       vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
03640     }
03641 }

03831 
03832 int (*show_function[])(struct vty *, struct ospf_lsa *) =
03833 {
03834   NULL,
03835   show_router_lsa_detail,
03836   show_network_lsa_detail,
03837   show_summary_lsa_detail,
03838   show_summary_asbr_lsa_detail,
03839   show_as_external_lsa_detail,
03840   show_func_dummy,
03841   show_as_nssa_lsa_detail,  /* almost same as external */
03842 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
03843   NULL,             /* type-8 */
03844   show_opaque_lsa_detail,
03845   show_opaque_lsa_detail,
03846   show_opaque_lsa_detail,
03847 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
03848 };
03849 
03850 static void
03851 show_lsa_prefix_set (struct vty *vty, struct prefix_ls *lp, struct in_addr *id,
03852              struct in_addr *adv_router)
03853 {
03854   memset (lp, 0, sizeof (struct prefix_ls));
03855   lp->family = 0;
03856   if (id == NULL)
03857     lp->prefixlen = 0;
03858   else if (adv_router == NULL)
03859     {
03860       lp->prefixlen = 32;
03861       lp->id = *id;
03862     }
03863   else
03864     {
03865       lp->prefixlen = 64;
03866       lp->id = *id;
03867       lp->adv_router = *adv_router;
03868     }
03869 }
03870 
03871 static void
03872 show_lsa_detail_proc (struct vty *vty, struct route_table *rt,
03873               struct in_addr *id, struct in_addr *adv_router)
03874 {
03875   struct prefix_ls lp;
03876   struct route_node *rn, *start;
03877   struct ospf_lsa *lsa;
03878 
03879   show_lsa_prefix_set (vty, &lp, id, adv_router);
03880   start = route_node_get (rt, (struct prefix *) &lp);
03881   if (start)
03882     {
03883       route_lock_node (start);
03884       for (rn = start; rn; rn = route_next_until (rn, start))
03885     if ((lsa = rn->info))
03886       {
03887         if (show_function[lsa->data->type] != NULL)
03888           show_function[lsa->data->type] (vty, lsa);
03889       }
03890       route_unlock_node (start);
03891     }
03892 }
03893 
03894 /* Show detail LSA information
03895    -- if id is NULL then show all LSAs. */
03896 static void
03897 show_lsa_detail (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf, int type,
03898          struct in_addr *id, struct in_addr *adv_router)
03899 {
03900   struct listnode *node;
03901   struct ospf_area *area;
03902   
03903   switch (type)
03904     {
03905     case OSPF_AS_EXTERNAL_LSA:
03906 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
03907     case OSPF_OPAQUE_AS_LSA:
03908 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
03909       vty_out (vty, "                %s %s%s",
03910                show_database_desc[type],
03911                VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
03912       show_lsa_detail_proc (vty, AS_LSDB (ospf, type), id, adv_router);
03913       break;
03914     default:
03915       for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->areas, node, area))
03916         {
03917           vty_out (vty, "%s                %s (Area %s)%s%s",
03918                    VTY_NEWLINE, show_database_desc[type],
03919                    ospf_area_desc_string (area), VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
03920           show_lsa_detail_proc (vty, AREA_LSDB (area, type), id, adv_router);
03921         }
03922       break;
03923     }
03924 }
03925 
03926 static void
03927 show_lsa_detail_adv_router_proc (struct vty *vty, struct route_table *rt,
03928                  struct in_addr *adv_router)
03929 {
03930   struct route_node *rn;
03931   struct ospf_lsa *lsa;
03932 
03933   for (rn = route_top (rt); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
03934     if ((lsa = rn->info))
03935       if (IPV4_ADDR_SAME (adv_router, &lsa->data->adv_router))
03936     {
03937       if (CHECK_FLAG (lsa->flags, OSPF_LSA_LOCAL_XLT))
03938         continue;
03939       if (show_function[lsa->data->type] != NULL)
03940         show_function[lsa->data->type] (vty, lsa);
03941     }
03942 }
03943 
03944 /* Show detail LSA information. */
03945 static void
03946 show_lsa_detail_adv_router (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf, int type,
03947                 struct in_addr *adv_router)
03948 {
03949   struct listnode *node;
03950   struct ospf_area *area;
03951 
03952   switch (type)
03953     {
03954     case OSPF_AS_EXTERNAL_LSA:
03955 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
03956     case OSPF_OPAQUE_AS_LSA:
03957 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
03958       vty_out (vty, "                %s %s%s",
03959                show_database_desc[type],
03960                VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
03961       show_lsa_detail_adv_router_proc (vty, AS_LSDB (ospf, type),
03962                                        adv_router);
03963       break;
03964     default:
03965       for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->areas, node, area))
03966         {
03967           vty_out (vty, "%s                %s (Area %s)%s%s",
03968                    VTY_NEWLINE, show_database_desc[type],
03969                    ospf_area_desc_string (area), VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
03970           show_lsa_detail_adv_router_proc (vty, AREA_LSDB (area, type),
03971                                            adv_router);
03972     }
03973       break;
03974     }
03975 }
03976 
03977 static void
03978 show_ip_ospf_database_summary (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf, int self)
03979 {
03980   struct ospf_lsa *lsa;
03981   struct route_node *rn;
03982   struct ospf_area *area;
03983   struct listnode *node;
03984   int type;
03985 
03986   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->areas, node, area))
03987     {
03988       for (type = OSPF_MIN_LSA; type < OSPF_MAX_LSA; type++)
03989     {
03990       switch (type)
03991         {
03992         case OSPF_AS_EXTERNAL_LSA:
03993 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
03994             case OSPF_OPAQUE_AS_LSA:
03995 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
03996           continue;
03997         default:
03998           break;
03999         }
04000           if (ospf_lsdb_count_self (area->lsdb, type) > 0 ||
04001               (!self && ospf_lsdb_count (area->lsdb, type) > 0))
04002             {
04003               vty_out (vty, "                %s (Area %s)%s%s",
04004                        show_database_desc[type],
04005                ospf_area_desc_string (area),
04006                        VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
04007               vty_out (vty, "%s%s", show_database_header[type], VTY_NEWLINE);
04008 
04009           LSDB_LOOP (AREA_LSDB (area, type), rn, lsa)
04010         show_lsa_summary (vty, lsa, self);
04011 
04012               vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
04013       }
04014     }
04015     }
04016 
04017   for (type = OSPF_MIN_LSA; type < OSPF_MAX_LSA; type++)
04018     {
04019       switch (type)
04020         {
04021           case OSPF_AS_EXTERNAL_LSA:
04022 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
04023           case OSPF_OPAQUE_AS_LSA:
04024 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
04025             break;
04026           default:
04027             continue;
04028         }
04029       if (ospf_lsdb_count_self (ospf->lsdb, type) ||
04030          (!self && ospf_lsdb_count (ospf->lsdb, type)))
04031         {
04032           vty_out (vty, "                %s%s%s",
04033            show_database_desc[type],
04034            VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
04035           vty_out (vty, "%s%s", show_database_header[type],
04036            VTY_NEWLINE);
04037 
04038       LSDB_LOOP (AS_LSDB (ospf, type), rn, lsa)
04039         show_lsa_summary (vty, lsa, self);
04040 
04041           vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
04042         }
04043     }
04044 
04045   vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
04046 }
04047 
04048 static void
04049 show_ip_ospf_database_maxage (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
04050 {
04051   struct listnode *node;
04052   struct ospf_lsa *lsa;
04053 
04054   vty_out (vty, "%s                MaxAge Link States:%s%s",
04055            VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
04056 
04057   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->maxage_lsa, node, lsa))
04058     {
04059       vty_out (vty, "Link type: %d%s", lsa->data->type, VTY_NEWLINE);
04060       vty_out (vty, "Link State ID: %s%s",
04061                inet_ntoa (lsa->data->id), VTY_NEWLINE);
04062       vty_out (vty, "Advertising Router: %s%s",
04063                inet_ntoa (lsa->data->adv_router), VTY_NEWLINE);
04064       vty_out (vty, "LSA lock count: %d%s", lsa->lock, VTY_NEWLINE);
04065       vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
04066     }
04067 }

04087     OSPF_LSA_TYPE_OPAQUE_CMD_STR

04100 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_database,
04101        show_ip_ospf_database_cmd,
04102        "show ip ospf database",
04103        SHOW_STR
04104        IP_STR
04105        "OSPF information\n"
04106        "Database summary\n")
04107 {
04108   struct ospf *ospf;
04109   int type, ret;
04110   struct in_addr id, adv_router;
04111 
04112   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
04113   if (ospf == NULL)
04114     {
04115       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
04116       return CMD_SUCCESS;
04117     }
04118 
04119   vty_out (vty, "%s       OSPF Router with ID (%s)%s%s", VTY_NEWLINE,
04120            inet_ntoa (ospf->router_id), VTY_NEWLINE, VTY_NEWLINE);
04121 
04122   /* Show all LSA. */
04123   if (argc == 0)
04124     {
04125       show_ip_ospf_database_summary (vty, ospf, 0);
04126       return CMD_SUCCESS;
04127     }
04128 
04129   /* Set database type to show. */
04130   if (strncmp (argv[0], "r", 1) == 0)
04131     type = OSPF_ROUTER_LSA;
04132   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "ne", 2) == 0)
04133     type = OSPF_NETWORK_LSA;
04134   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "ns", 2) == 0)
04135     type = OSPF_AS_NSSA_LSA;
04136   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "su", 2) == 0)
04137     type = OSPF_SUMMARY_LSA;
04138   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "a", 1) == 0)
04139     type = OSPF_ASBR_SUMMARY_LSA;
04140   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "e", 1) == 0)
04141     type = OSPF_AS_EXTERNAL_LSA;
04142   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "se", 2) == 0)
04143     {
04144       show_ip_ospf_database_summary (vty, ospf, 1);
04145       return CMD_SUCCESS;
04146     }
04147   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "m", 1) == 0)
04148     {
04149       show_ip_ospf_database_maxage (vty, ospf);
04150       return CMD_SUCCESS;
04151     }
04152 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
04153   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "opaque-l", 8) == 0)
04154     type = OSPF_OPAQUE_LINK_LSA;
04155   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "opaque-ar", 9) == 0)
04156     type = OSPF_OPAQUE_AREA_LSA;
04157   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "opaque-as", 9) == 0)
04158     type = OSPF_OPAQUE_AS_LSA;
04159 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
04160   else
04161     return CMD_WARNING;
04162 
04163   /* `show ip ospf database LSA'. */
04164   if (argc == 1)
04165     show_lsa_detail (vty, ospf, type, NULL, NULL);
04166   else if (argc >= 2)
04167     {
04168       ret = inet_aton (argv[1], &id);
04169       if (!ret)
04170     return CMD_WARNING;
04171       
04172       /* `show ip ospf database LSA ID'. */
04173       if (argc == 2)
04174     show_lsa_detail (vty, ospf, type, &id, NULL);
04175       /* `show ip ospf database LSA ID adv-router ADV_ROUTER'. */
04176       else if (argc == 3)
04177     {
04178       if (strncmp (argv[2], "s", 1) == 0)
04179         adv_router = ospf->router_id;
04180       else
04181         {
04182           ret = inet_aton (argv[2], &adv_router);
04183           if (!ret)
04184         return CMD_WARNING;
04185         }
04186       show_lsa_detail (vty, ospf, type, &id, &adv_router);
04187     }
04188     }
04189 
04190   return CMD_SUCCESS;
04191 }

04316 DEFUN (ip_ospf_authentication_args,
04317        ip_ospf_authentication_args_addr_cmd,
04318        "ip ospf authentication (null|message-digest) A.B.C.D",
04319        "IP Information\n"
04320        "OSPF interface commands\n"
04321        "Enable authentication on this interface\n"
04322        "Use null authentication\n"
04323        "Use message-digest authentication\n"
04324        "Address of interface")
04325 {
04326   struct interface *ifp;
04327   struct in_addr addr;
04328   int ret;
04329   struct ospf_if_params *params;
04330   
04331   ifp = vty->index;
04332   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
04333 
04334   if (argc == 2)
04335     {
04336       ret = inet_aton(argv[1], &addr);
04337       if (!ret)
04338     {
04339       vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
04340            VTY_NEWLINE);
04341       return CMD_WARNING;
04342     }
04343 
04344       params = ospf_get_if_params (ifp, addr);
04345       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
04346     }
04347 
04348   /* Handle null authentication */
04349   if ( argv[0][0] == 'n' )
04350     {
04351       SET_IF_PARAM (params, auth_type);
04352       params->auth_type = OSPF_AUTH_NULL;
04353       return CMD_SUCCESS;
04354     }
04355 
04356   /* Handle message-digest authentication */
04357   if ( argv[0][0] == 'm' )
04358     {
04359       SET_IF_PARAM (params, auth_type);
04360       params->auth_type = OSPF_AUTH_CRYPTOGRAPHIC;
04361       return CMD_SUCCESS;
04362     }
04363 
04364   vty_out (vty, "You shouldn't get here!%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
04365   return CMD_WARNING;
04366 }

04473        ip_ospf_authentication_key_addr_cmd,
04474        "ip ospf authentication-key AUTH_KEY A.B.C.D",
04475        "IP Information\n"
04476        "OSPF interface commands\n"
04477        "Authentication password (key)\n"
04478        "The OSPF password (key)\n"
04479        "Address of interface")
04480 {
04481   struct interface *ifp;
04482   struct in_addr addr;
04483   int ret;
04484   struct ospf_if_params *params;
04485   
04486   ifp = vty->index;
04487   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
04488 
04489   if (argc == 2)
04490     {
04491       ret = inet_aton(argv[1], &addr);
04492       if (!ret)
04493     {
04494       vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
04495            VTY_NEWLINE);
04496       return CMD_WARNING;
04497     }
04498 
04499       params = ospf_get_if_params (ifp, addr);
04500       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
04501     }
04502 
04503 
04504   memset (params->auth_simple, 0, OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE_SIZE + 1);
04505   strncpy ((char *) params->auth_simple, argv[0], OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE_SIZE);
04506   SET_IF_PARAM (params, auth_simple);
04507 
04508   return CMD_SUCCESS;
04509 }

04585 DEFUN (ip_ospf_message_digest_key,
04586        ip_ospf_message_digest_key_addr_cmd,
04587        "ip ospf message-digest-key <1-255> md5 KEY A.B.C.D",
04588        "IP Information\n"
04589        "OSPF interface commands\n"
04590        "Message digest authentication password (key)\n"
04591        "Key ID\n"
04592        "Use MD5 algorithm\n"
04593        "The OSPF password (key)"
04594        "Address of interface")
04595 {
04596   struct interface *ifp;
04597   struct crypt_key *ck;
04598   u_char key_id;
04599   struct in_addr addr;
04600   int ret;
04601   struct ospf_if_params *params;
04602   
04603   ifp = vty->index;
04604   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
04605 
04606   if (argc == 3)
04607     {
04608       ret = inet_aton(argv[2], &addr);
04609       if (!ret)
04610     {
04611       vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
04612            VTY_NEWLINE);
04613       return CMD_WARNING;
04614     }
04615 
04616       params = ospf_get_if_params (ifp, addr);
04617       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
04618     }
04619 
04620   key_id = strtol (argv[0], NULL, 10);
04621   if (ospf_crypt_key_lookup (params->auth_crypt, key_id) != NULL)
04622     {
04623       vty_out (vty, "OSPF: Key %d already exists%s", key_id, VTY_NEWLINE);
04624       return CMD_WARNING;
04625     }
04626 
04627   ck = ospf_crypt_key_new ();
04628   ck->key_id = (u_char) key_id;
04629   memset (ck->auth_key, 0, OSPF_AUTH_MD5_SIZE+1);
04630   strncpy ((char *) ck->auth_key, argv[1], OSPF_AUTH_MD5_SIZE);
04631 
04632   ospf_crypt_key_add (params->auth_crypt, ck);
04633   SET_IF_PARAM (params, auth_crypt);
04634   
04635   return CMD_SUCCESS;
04636 }

04728 DEFUN (ip_ospf_cost,
04729        ip_ospf_cost_u32_inet4_cmd,

04731        "IP Information\n"
04732        "OSPF interface commands\n"
04733        "Interface cost\n"
04734        "Cost\n"
04735        "Address of interface")
04736 {
04737   struct interface *ifp = vty->index;
04738   u_int32_t cost;
04739   struct in_addr addr;
04740   int ret;

04742       
04743   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
04744 
04745   cost = strtol (argv[0], NULL, 10);
04746 
04747   /* cost range is <1-65535>. */
04748   if (cost < 1 || cost > 65535)
04749     {
04750       vty_out (vty, "Interface output cost is invalid%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
04751       return CMD_WARNING;
04752     }
04753 
04754   if (argc == 2)
04755     {

04762     }

04764       params = ospf_get_if_params (ifp, addr);
04765       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
04766     }
04767 
04768   SET_IF_PARAM (params, output_cost_cmd);
04769   params->output_cost_cmd = cost;
04770 
04771   ospf_if_recalculate_output_cost (ifp);
04772     
04773   return CMD_SUCCESS;
04774 }

04867 DEFUN (no_ip_ospf_cost2,
04868        no_ip_ospf_cost_u32_cmd,
04869        "no ip ospf cost <1-65535>",
04870        NO_STR
04871        "IP Information\n"
04872        "OSPF interface commands\n"

04875 {
04876   struct interface *ifp = vty->index;
04877   struct in_addr addr;
04878   u_int32_t cost;

04880   struct ospf_if_params *params;
04881 
04882   ifp = vty->index;
04883   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
04884 
04885   /* According to the semantics we are mimicking "no ip ospf cost N" is
04886    * always treated as "no ip ospf cost" regardless of the actual value
04887    * of N already configured for the interface. Thus the first argument
04888    * is always checked to be a number, but is ignored after that.
04889    */
04890   cost = strtol (argv[0], NULL, 10);
04891   if (cost < 1 || cost > 65535)
04892     {
04893       vty_out (vty, "Interface output cost is invalid%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
04894       return CMD_WARNING;
04895     }
04896 
04897   if (argc == 2)
04898     {
04899       ret = inet_aton(argv[1], &addr);
04900       if (!ret)
04901     {
04902       vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
04903            VTY_NEWLINE);
04904       return CMD_WARNING;
04905     }
04906 
04907       params = ospf_lookup_if_params (ifp, addr);
04908       if (params == NULL)
04909     return CMD_SUCCESS;
04910     }
04911 
04912   UNSET_IF_PARAM (params, output_cost_cmd);
04913 
04914   if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
04915     {
04916       ospf_free_if_params (ifp, addr);
04917       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
04918     }
04919 
04920   ospf_if_recalculate_output_cost (ifp);
04921 
04922   return CMD_SUCCESS;
04923 }

04952 static void
04953 ospf_nbr_timer_update (struct ospf_interface *oi)
04954 {
04955   struct route_node *rn;
04956   struct ospf_neighbor *nbr;
04957 
04958   for (rn = route_top (oi->nbrs); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
04959     if ((nbr = rn->info))
04960       {
04961     nbr->v_inactivity = OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, v_wait);
04962     nbr->v_db_desc = OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, retransmit_interval);
04963     nbr->v_ls_req = OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, retransmit_interval);
04964     nbr->v_ls_upd = OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, retransmit_interval);
04965       }
04966 }
04967 
04968 static int
04969 ospf_vty_dead_interval_set (struct vty *vty, const char *interval_str,
04970                             const char *nbr_str,
04971                             const char *fast_hello_str)
04972 {
04973   struct interface *ifp = vty->index;
04974   u_int32_t seconds;
04975   u_char hellomult;
04976   struct in_addr addr;
04977   int ret;
04978   struct ospf_if_params *params;
04979   struct ospf_interface *oi;
04980   struct route_node *rn;
04981       
04982   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
04983   
04984   if (nbr_str)
04985     {
04986       ret = inet_aton(nbr_str, &addr);
04987       if (!ret)
04988     {
04989       vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
04990            VTY_NEWLINE);
04991       return CMD_WARNING;
04992     }
04993 
04994       params = ospf_get_if_params (ifp, addr);
04995       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
04996     }
04997 
04998   if (interval_str)
04999     {
05000       VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("Router Dead Interval", seconds, interval_str,
05001                              1, 65535);
05002                              
05003       /* reset fast_hello too, just to be sure */
05004       UNSET_IF_PARAM (params, fast_hello);
05005       params->fast_hello = OSPF_FAST_HELLO_DEFAULT;
05006     }
05007   else if (fast_hello_str)
05008     {
05009       VTY_GET_INTEGER_RANGE ("Hello Multiplier", hellomult, fast_hello_str,
05010                              1, 10);
05011       /* 1s dead-interval with sub-second hellos desired */
05012       seconds = OSPF_ROUTER_DEAD_INTERVAL_MINIMAL;
05013       SET_IF_PARAM (params, fast_hello);
05014       params->fast_hello = hellomult;
05015     }
05016   else
05017     {
05018       vty_out (vty, "Please specify dead-interval or hello-multiplier%s",
05019               VTY_NEWLINE);
05020       return CMD_WARNING;
05021     }
05022     
05023   SET_IF_PARAM (params, v_wait);
05024   params->v_wait = seconds;
05025   
05026   /* Update timer values in neighbor structure. */
05027   if (nbr_str)
05028     {
05029       struct ospf *ospf;
05030       if ((ospf = ospf_lookup()))
05031     {
05032       oi = ospf_if_lookup_by_local_addr (ospf, ifp, addr);
05033       if (oi)
05034         ospf_nbr_timer_update (oi);
05035     }
05036     }
05037   else
05038     {
05039       for (rn = route_top (IF_OIFS (ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
05040     if ((oi = rn->info))
05041       ospf_nbr_timer_update (oi);
05042     }
05043 
05044   return CMD_SUCCESS;
05045 }
05046 
05047 
05048 DEFUN (ip_ospf_dead_interval,
05049        ip_ospf_dead_interval_addr_cmd,
05050        "ip ospf dead-interval <1-65535> A.B.C.D",
05051        "IP Information\n"
05052        "OSPF interface commands\n"
05053        "Interval after which a neighbor is declared dead\n"
05054        "Seconds\n"
05055        "Address of interface\n")
05056 {
05057   if (argc == 2)
05058     return ospf_vty_dead_interval_set (vty, argv[0], argv[1], NULL);
05059   else
05060     return ospf_vty_dead_interval_set (vty, argv[0], NULL, NULL);
05061 }

05146     {
05147       ospf_free_if_params (ifp, addr);
05148       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
05149     }
05150 
05151   /* Update timer values in neighbor structure. */
05152   if (argc == 1)
05153     {
05154       struct ospf *ospf;
05155       
05156       if ((ospf = ospf_lookup()))
05157     {
05158       oi = ospf_if_lookup_by_local_addr (ospf, ifp, addr);
05159       if (oi)
05160         ospf_nbr_timer_update (oi);
05161     }
05162     }
05163   else
05164     {
05165       for (rn = route_top (IF_OIFS (ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
05166     if ((oi = rn->info))
05167       ospf_nbr_timer_update (oi);
05168     }
05169 
05170   return CMD_SUCCESS;
05171 }

05308 DEFUN (ip_ospf_network,
05309        ip_ospf_network_cmd,
05310        "ip ospf network (broadcast|non-broadcast|point-to-multipoint|point-to-point)",
05311        "IP Information\n"
05312        "OSPF interface commands\n"
05313        "Network type\n"
05314        "Specify OSPF broadcast multi-access network\n"
05315        "Specify OSPF NBMA network\n"
05316        "Specify OSPF point-to-multipoint network\n"
05317        "Specify OSPF point-to-point network\n")
05318 {
05319   struct interface *ifp = vty->index;
05320   int old_type = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->type;
05321   struct route_node *rn;
05322   
05323   if (strncmp (argv[0], "b", 1) == 0)
05324     IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->type = OSPF_IFTYPE_BROADCAST;
05325   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "n", 1) == 0)
05326     IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->type = OSPF_IFTYPE_NBMA;
05327   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "point-to-m", 10) == 0)
05328     IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->type = OSPF_IFTYPE_POINTOMULTIPOINT;
05329   else if (strncmp (argv[0], "point-to-p", 10) == 0)
05330     IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->type = OSPF_IFTYPE_POINTOPOINT;
05331 
05332   if (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->type == old_type)
05333     return CMD_SUCCESS;
05334 
05335   SET_IF_PARAM (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), type);
05336 
05337   for (rn = route_top (IF_OIFS (ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
05338     {
05339       struct ospf_interface *oi = rn->info;
05340 
05341       if (!oi)
05342     continue;
05343       
05344       oi->type = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->type;
05345       
05346       if (oi->state > ISM_Down)
05347     {
05348       OSPF_ISM_EVENT_EXECUTE (oi, ISM_InterfaceDown);
05349       OSPF_ISM_EVENT_EXECUTE (oi, ISM_InterfaceUp);
05350     }
05351     }
05352 
05353   return CMD_SUCCESS;
05354 }
05355 
05356 ALIAS (ip_ospf_network,
05357        ospf_network_cmd,
05358        "ospf network (broadcast|non-broadcast|point-to-multipoint|point-to-point)",
05359        "OSPF interface commands\n"
05360        "Network type\n"
05361        "Specify OSPF broadcast multi-access network\n"
05362        "Specify OSPF NBMA network\n"
05363        "Specify OSPF point-to-multipoint network\n"
05364        "Specify OSPF point-to-point network\n")

05395       OSPF_ISM_EVENT_EXECUTE (oi, ISM_InterfaceUp);

05409 DEFUN (ip_ospf_priority,
05410        ip_ospf_priority_addr_cmd,
05411        "ip ospf priority <0-255> A.B.C.D",
05412        "IP Information\n"
05413        "OSPF interface commands\n"
05414        "Router priority\n"
05415        "Priority\n"
05416        "Address of interface")
05417 {
05418   struct interface *ifp = vty->index;
05419   u_int32_t priority;
05420   struct route_node *rn;
05421   struct in_addr addr;
05422   int ret;
05423   struct ospf_if_params *params;
05424       
05425   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
05426 
05427   priority = strtol (argv[0], NULL, 10);
05428   
05429   /* Router Priority range is <0-255>. */
05430   if (priority < 0 || priority > 255)
05431     {
05432       vty_out (vty, "Router Priority is invalid%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
05433       return CMD_WARNING;
05434     }
05435 
05436   if (argc == 2)
05437     {
05438       ret = inet_aton(argv[1], &addr);
05439       if (!ret)
05440     {
05441       vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
05442            VTY_NEWLINE);
05443       return CMD_WARNING;
05444     }
05445 
05446       params = ospf_get_if_params (ifp, addr);
05447       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
05448     }
05449   
05450   SET_IF_PARAM (params, priority);
05451   params->priority = priority;
05452 
05453   for (rn = route_top (IF_OIFS (ifp)); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
05454     {
05455       struct ospf_interface *oi = rn->info;
05456       
05457       if (!oi)
05458     continue;
05459       
05460 
05461       if (PRIORITY (oi) != OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, priority))
05462     {
05463       PRIORITY (oi) = OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, priority);
05464       OSPF_ISM_EVENT_SCHEDULE (oi, ISM_NeighborChange);
05465     }
05466     }
05467   
05468   return CMD_SUCCESS;
05469 }

05803        "redistribute " QUAGGA_REDIST_STR_OSPFD

06383        "OSPF metric type for default routes\n"
06384        "Set OSPF External Type 1 metrics\n"
06385        "Set OSPF External Type 2 metrics\n"
06386        "OSPF default metric\n"
06387        "OSPF metric\n"
06388        "Route map reference\n"
06389        "Pointer to route-map entries\n")
06390 {
06391   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
06392   int type = -1;
06393   int metric = -1;
06394 
06395   /* Get metric type. */
06396   if (argc >= 1)
06397     if (!str2metric_type (argv[0], &type))
06398       return CMD_WARNING;
06399 
06400   /* Get metric value. */
06401   if (argc >= 2)
06402     if (!str2metric (argv[1], &metric))
06403       return CMD_WARNING;
06404 
06405   if (argc == 3)
06406     ospf_routemap_set (ospf, DEFAULT_ROUTE, argv[2]);
06407   else
06408     ospf_routemap_unset (ospf, DEFAULT_ROUTE);
06409 
06410   return ospf_redistribute_default_set (ospf, DEFAULT_ORIGINATE_ALWAYS,
06411                     type, metric);
06412 }

06465 DEFUN (no_ospf_default_information_originate,
06466        no_ospf_default_information_originate_cmd,
06467        "no default-information originate",
06468        NO_STR
06469        "Control distribution of default information\n"
06470        "Distribute a default route\n")
06471 {
06472   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
06473   struct prefix_ipv4 p;
06474     
06475   p.family = AF_INET;
06476   p.prefix.s_addr = 0;
06477   p.prefixlen = 0;
06478 
06479   ospf_external_lsa_flush (ospf, DEFAULT_ROUTE, &p, 0);
06480 
06481   if (EXTERNAL_INFO (DEFAULT_ROUTE)) {
06482     ospf_external_info_delete (DEFAULT_ROUTE, p);
06483     route_table_finish (EXTERNAL_INFO (DEFAULT_ROUTE));
06484     EXTERNAL_INFO (DEFAULT_ROUTE) = NULL;
06485   }
06486 
06487   ospf_routemap_unset (ospf, DEFAULT_ROUTE);
06488   return ospf_redistribute_default_unset (ospf);
06489 }

06911 DEFUN (ip_ospf_mtu_ignore,
06912        ip_ospf_mtu_ignore_addr_cmd,
06913        "ip ospf mtu-ignore A.B.C.D",
06914        "IP Information\n"
06915        "OSPF interface commands\n"
06916        "Disable mtu mismatch detection\n"
06917        "Address of interface")
06918 {
06919   struct interface *ifp = vty->index;
06920   struct in_addr addr;
06921   int ret;
06922        
06923   struct ospf_if_params *params;
06924   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
06925      
06926   if (argc == 1)
06927     {
06928       ret = inet_aton(argv[0], &addr);
06929       if (!ret)
06930         {
06931           vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
06932                   VTY_NEWLINE);
06933           return CMD_WARNING;
06934         }
06935       params = ospf_get_if_params (ifp, addr);
06936       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
06937     }
06938   params->mtu_ignore = 1;
06939   if (params->mtu_ignore != OSPF_MTU_IGNORE_DEFAULT)
06940     SET_IF_PARAM (params, mtu_ignore);
06941   else 
06942     {
06943       UNSET_IF_PARAM (params, mtu_ignore);
06944       if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
06945         {
06946           ospf_free_if_params (ifp, addr);
06947           ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
06948         }
06949     }
06950   return CMD_SUCCESS;
06951 }
06952 
06953 ALIAS (ip_ospf_mtu_ignore,
06954       ip_ospf_mtu_ignore_cmd,
06955       "ip ospf mtu-ignore",
06956       "IP Information\n"
06957       "OSPF interface commands\n"
06958       "Disable mtu mismatch detection\n")
06959 
06960     
06961 DEFUN (no_ip_ospf_mtu_ignore,
06962        no_ip_ospf_mtu_ignore_addr_cmd,
06963        "no ip ospf mtu-ignore A.B.C.D",
06964        "IP Information\n"
06965        "OSPF interface commands\n"
06966        "Disable mtu mismatch detection\n"
06967        "Address of interface")
06968 {
06969   struct interface *ifp = vty->index;
06970   struct in_addr addr;
06971   int ret;
06972        
06973   struct ospf_if_params *params;
06974   params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
06975      
06976   if (argc == 1)
06977     {
06978       ret = inet_aton(argv[0], &addr);
06979       if (!ret)
06980         {
06981           vty_out (vty, "Please specify interface address by A.B.C.D%s",
06982                   VTY_NEWLINE);
06983           return CMD_WARNING;
06984         }
06985       params = ospf_get_if_params (ifp, addr);
06986       ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
06987     }
06988   params->mtu_ignore = 0;
06989   if (params->mtu_ignore != OSPF_MTU_IGNORE_DEFAULT)
06990     SET_IF_PARAM (params, mtu_ignore);
06991   else 
06992     {
06993       UNSET_IF_PARAM (params, mtu_ignore);
06994       if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
06995         {
06996           ospf_free_if_params (ifp, addr);
06997           ospf_if_update_params (ifp, addr);
06998         }
06999     }
07000   return CMD_SUCCESS;

07010 DEFUN (ospf_max_metric_router_lsa_admin,
07011        ospf_max_metric_router_lsa_admin_cmd,
07012        "max-metric router-lsa administrative",
07013        "OSPF maximum / infinite-distance metric\n"
07014        "Advertise own Router-LSA with infinite distance (stub router)\n"
07015        "Administratively applied, for an indefinite period\n")
07016 {
07017   struct listnode *ln;
07018   struct ospf_area *area;
07019   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
07020     
07021   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->areas, ln, area))
07022     {
07023       SET_FLAG (area->stub_router_state, OSPF_AREA_ADMIN_STUB_ROUTED);
07024       
07025       if (!CHECK_FLAG (area->stub_router_state, OSPF_AREA_IS_STUB_ROUTED))
07026           ospf_router_lsa_timer_add (area);
07027     }
07028   return CMD_SUCCESS;
07029 }

07031 DEFUN (no_ospf_max_metric_router_lsa_admin,
07032        no_ospf_max_metric_router_lsa_admin_cmd,
07033        "no max-metric router-lsa administrative",
07034        NO_STR
07035        "OSPF maximum / infinite-distance metric\n"
07036        "Advertise own Router-LSA with infinite distance (stub router)\n"
07037        "Administratively applied, for an indefinite period\n")
07038 {
07039   struct listnode *ln;
07040   struct ospf_area *area;
07041   struct ospf *ospf = vty->index;
07042     
07043   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->areas, ln, area))
07044     {
07045       UNSET_FLAG (area->stub_router_state, OSPF_AREA_ADMIN_STUB_ROUTED);
07046       
07047       /* Don't trample on the start-up stub timer */
07048       if (CHECK_FLAG (area->stub_router_state, OSPF_AREA_IS_STUB_ROUTED)
07049           && !area->t_stub_router)
07050         {
07051           UNSET_FLAG (area->stub_router_state, OSPF_AREA_IS_STUB_ROUTED);
07052           ospf_router_lsa_timer_add (area);
07053         }
07054     }
07055   return CMD_SUCCESS;
07056 }

07086        "OSPF maximum / infinite-distance metric\n"

07103         {
07104           UNSET_FLAG (area->stub_router_state, OSPF_AREA_IS_STUB_ROUTED);
07105           ospf_router_lsa_timer_add (area);
07106         }
07107     }
07108   return CMD_SUCCESS;

07150 static void
07151 config_write_stub_router (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
07152 {
07153   struct listnode *ln;
07154   struct ospf_area *area;
07155   
07156   if (ospf->stub_router_startup_time != OSPF_STUB_ROUTER_UNCONFIGURED)
07157     vty_out (vty, " max-metric router-lsa on-startup %u%s",
07158              ospf->stub_router_startup_time, VTY_NEWLINE);
07159   if (ospf->stub_router_shutdown_time != OSPF_STUB_ROUTER_UNCONFIGURED)
07160     vty_out (vty, " max-metric router-lsa on-shutdown %u%s",
07161              ospf->stub_router_shutdown_time, VTY_NEWLINE);
07162   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->areas, ln, area))
07163     {
07164       if (CHECK_FLAG (area->stub_router_state, OSPF_AREA_ADMIN_STUB_ROUTED))
07165         {
07166           vty_out (vty, " max-metric router-lsa administrative%s",
07167                    VTY_NEWLINE);
07168           break;
07169         }
07170     }
07171   return;
07172 }
07173 
07174 static void
07175 show_ip_ospf_route_network (struct vty *vty, struct route_table *rt)
07176 {
07177   struct route_node *rn;
07178   struct ospf_route *or;
07179   struct listnode *pnode, *pnnode;
07180   struct ospf_path *path;
07181 
07182   vty_out (vty, "============ OSPF network routing table ============%s",
07183        VTY_NEWLINE);
07184 
07185   for (rn = route_top (rt); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
07186     if ((or = rn->info) != NULL)
07187       {
07188     char buf1[19];
07189     snprintf (buf1, 19, "%s/%d",
07190           inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4), rn->p.prefixlen);
07191 
07192     switch (or->path_type)
07193       {
07194       case OSPF_PATH_INTER_AREA:
07195         if (or->type == OSPF_DESTINATION_NETWORK)
07196           vty_out (vty, "N IA %-18s    [%d] area: %s%s", buf1, or->cost,
07197                inet_ntoa (or->u.std.area_id), VTY_NEWLINE);
07198         else if (or->type == OSPF_DESTINATION_DISCARD)
07199           vty_out (vty, "D IA %-18s    Discard entry%s", buf1, VTY_NEWLINE);
07200         break;
07201       case OSPF_PATH_INTRA_AREA:
07202         vty_out (vty, "N    %-18s    [%d] area: %s%s", buf1, or->cost,
07203              inet_ntoa (or->u.std.area_id), VTY_NEWLINE);
07204         break;
07205       default:
07206         break;
07207       }
07208 
07209         if (or->type == OSPF_DESTINATION_NETWORK)
07210           for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS (or->paths, pnode, pnnode, path))
07211             {
07212               if (if_lookup_by_index(path->ifindex))
07213                 {
07214                   if (path->nexthop.s_addr == 0)
07215                     vty_out (vty, "%24s   directly attached to %s%s",
07216                              "", ifindex2ifname (path->ifindex), VTY_NEWLINE);
07217                   else
07218                     vty_out (vty, "%24s   via %s, %s%s", "",
07219                              inet_ntoa (path->nexthop),
07220                  ifindex2ifname (path->ifindex), VTY_NEWLINE);
07221                 }
07222             }
07223       }
07224   vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07225 }
07226 
07227 static void
07228 show_ip_ospf_route_router (struct vty *vty, struct route_table *rtrs)
07229 {
07230   struct route_node *rn;
07231   struct ospf_route *or;
07232   struct listnode *pnode;
07233   struct listnode *node;
07234   struct ospf_path *path;
07235 
07236   vty_out (vty, "============ OSPF router routing table =============%s",
07237        VTY_NEWLINE);
07238   for (rn = route_top (rtrs); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
07239     if (rn->info)
07240       {
07241     int flag = 0;
07242 
07243     vty_out (vty, "R    %-15s    ", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07244 
07245     for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO ((struct list *)rn->info, node, or))
07246           {
07247             if (flag++)
07248           vty_out (vty, "%24s", "");
07249 
07250             /* Show path. */
07251             vty_out (vty, "%s [%d] area: %s",
07252                      (or->path_type == OSPF_PATH_INTER_AREA ? "IA" : "  "),
07253                      or->cost, inet_ntoa (or->u.std.area_id));
07254             /* Show flags. */
07255             vty_out (vty, "%s%s%s",
07256                      (or->u.std.flags & ROUTER_LSA_BORDER ? ", ABR" : ""),
07257                      (or->u.std.flags & ROUTER_LSA_EXTERNAL ? ", ASBR" : ""),
07258                      VTY_NEWLINE);
07259                   
07260                   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (or->paths, pnode, path))
07261                     {
07262               if (if_lookup_by_index(path->ifindex))
07263             {
07264               if (path->nexthop.s_addr == 0)
07265                 vty_out (vty, "%24s   directly attached to %s%s",
07266                      "", ifindex2ifname (path->ifindex),
07267                      VTY_NEWLINE);
07268               else
07269                 vty_out (vty, "%24s   via %s, %s%s", "",
07270                      inet_ntoa (path->nexthop),
07271                      ifindex2ifname (path->ifindex),
07272                      VTY_NEWLINE);
07273             }
07274                     }
07275           }
07276       }
07277   vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07278 }
07279 
07280 static void
07281 show_ip_ospf_route_external (struct vty *vty, struct route_table *rt)
07282 {
07283   struct route_node *rn;
07284   struct ospf_route *er;
07285   struct listnode *pnode, *pnnode;
07286   struct ospf_path *path;
07287 
07288   vty_out (vty, "============ OSPF external routing table ===========%s",
07289        VTY_NEWLINE);
07290   for (rn = route_top (rt); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
07291     if ((er = rn->info) != NULL)
07292       {
07293     char buf1[19];
07294     snprintf (buf1, 19, "%s/%d",
07295           inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4), rn->p.prefixlen);
07296 
07297     switch (er->path_type)
07298       {
07299       case OSPF_PATH_TYPE1_EXTERNAL:
07300         vty_out (vty, "N E1 %-18s    [%d] tag: %u%s", buf1,
07301              er->cost, er->u.ext.tag, VTY_NEWLINE);
07302         break;
07303       case OSPF_PATH_TYPE2_EXTERNAL:
07304         vty_out (vty, "N E2 %-18s    [%d/%d] tag: %u%s", buf1, er->cost,
07305              er->u.ext.type2_cost, er->u.ext.tag, VTY_NEWLINE);
07306         break;
07307       }
07308 
07309         for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS (er->paths, pnode, pnnode, path))
07310           {
07311             if (if_lookup_by_index(path->ifindex))
07312               {
07313                 if (path->nexthop.s_addr == 0)
07314                   vty_out (vty, "%24s   directly attached to %s%s",
07315                            "", ifindex2ifname (path->ifindex), VTY_NEWLINE);
07316                 else
07317                   vty_out (vty, "%24s   via %s, %s%s", "",
07318                            inet_ntoa (path->nexthop),
07319                ifindex2ifname (path->ifindex),
07320                            VTY_NEWLINE);
07321               }
07322            }
07323         }
07324   vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07325 }

07327 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_border_routers,
07328        show_ip_ospf_border_routers_cmd,
07329        "show ip ospf border-routers",
07330        SHOW_STR
07331        IP_STR
07332        "show all the ABR's and ASBR's\n"
07333        "for this area\n")
07334 {
07335   struct ospf *ospf;
07336 
07337   if ((ospf = ospf_lookup ()) == NULL)
07338     {
07339       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07340       return CMD_SUCCESS;
07341     }
07342 
07343   if (ospf->new_table == NULL)
07344     {
07345       vty_out (vty, "No OSPF routing information exist%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07346       return CMD_SUCCESS;
07347     }
07348 
07349   /* Show Network routes.
07350   show_ip_ospf_route_network (vty, ospf->new_table);   */
07351 
07352   /* Show Router routes. */
07353   show_ip_ospf_route_router (vty, ospf->new_rtrs);
07354 
07355   return CMD_SUCCESS;
07356 }
07357 
07358 DEFUN (show_ip_ospf_route,
07359        show_ip_ospf_route_cmd,
07360        "show ip ospf route",
07361        SHOW_STR
07362        IP_STR
07363        "OSPF information\n"
07364        "OSPF routing table\n")
07365 {
07366   struct ospf *ospf;
07367 
07368   if ((ospf = ospf_lookup ()) == NULL)
07369     {
07370       vty_out (vty, " OSPF Routing Process not enabled%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07371       return CMD_SUCCESS;
07372     }
07373 
07374   if (ospf->new_table == NULL)
07375     {
07376       vty_out (vty, "No OSPF routing information exist%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07377       return CMD_SUCCESS;
07378     }
07379 
07380   /* Show Network routes. */
07381   show_ip_ospf_route_network (vty, ospf->new_table);
07382 
07383   /* Show Router routes. */
07384   show_ip_ospf_route_router (vty, ospf->new_rtrs);
07385 
07386   /* Show AS External routes. */
07387   show_ip_ospf_route_external (vty, ospf->old_external_route);
07388 
07389   return CMD_SUCCESS;
07390 }

07410 static void
07411 area_id2str (char *buf, int length, struct ospf_area *area)
07412 {
07413   memset (buf, 0, length);
07414 
07415   if (area->format == OSPF_AREA_ID_FORMAT_ADDRESS)
07416     strncpy (buf, inet_ntoa (area->area_id), length);
07417   else
07418     sprintf (buf, "%lu", (unsigned long) ntohl (area->area_id.s_addr));
07419 }
07420 
07421 
07422 const char *ospf_int_type_str[] = 
07423 {
07424   "unknown",        /* should never be used. */
07425   "point-to-point",
07426   "broadcast",
07427   "non-broadcast",
07428   "point-to-multipoint",
07429   "virtual-link",   /* should never be used. */
07430   "loopback"
07431 };
07432 
07433 /* Configuration write function for ospfd. */
07434 static int
07435 config_write_interface (struct vty *vty)
07436 {
07437   struct listnode *n1, *n2;
07438   struct interface *ifp;
07439   struct crypt_key *ck;
07440   int write = 0;
07441   struct route_node *rn = NULL;
07442   struct ospf_if_params *params;
07443 
07444   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (iflist, n1, ifp))
07445     {
07446       if (memcmp (ifp->name, "VLINK", 5) == 0)
07447     continue;
07448 
07449       vty_out (vty, "!%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07450       vty_out (vty, "interface %s%s", ifp->name,
07451                VTY_NEWLINE);
07452       if (ifp->desc)
07453         vty_out (vty, " description %s%s", ifp->desc,
07454                VTY_NEWLINE);
07455 
07456       write++;
07457 
07458       params = IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp);
07459       
07460       do {
07461     /* Interface Network print. */
07462     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, type) &&
07463         params->type != OSPF_IFTYPE_LOOPBACK)
07464       {
07465         if (params->type != ospf_default_iftype(ifp))
07466           {
07467         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf network %s",
07468              ospf_int_type_str[params->type]);
07469         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07470           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07471         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07472           }
07473       }
07474     
07475     /* OSPF interface authentication print */
07476     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, auth_type) &&
07477         params->auth_type != OSPF_AUTH_NOTSET)
07478       {
07479         const char *auth_str;
07480         
07481         /* Translation tables are not that much help here due to syntax
07482            of the simple option */
07483         switch (params->auth_type)
07484           {
07485         
07486           case OSPF_AUTH_NULL:
07487         auth_str = " null";
07488         break;
07489         
07490           case OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE:
07491         auth_str = "";
07492         break;
07493         
07494           case OSPF_AUTH_CRYPTOGRAPHIC:
07495         auth_str = " message-digest";
07496         break;
07497         
07498           default:
07499         auth_str = "";
07500         break;
07501           }
07502         
07503         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf authentication%s", auth_str);
07504         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07505           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07506         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07507       }
07508 
07509     /* Simple Authentication Password print. */
07510     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, auth_simple) &&
07511         params->auth_simple[0] != '\0')
07512       {
07513         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf authentication-key %s",
07514              params->auth_simple);
07515         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07516           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07517         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07518       }
07519     
07520     /* Cryptographic Authentication Key print. */
07521     for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (params->auth_crypt, n2, ck))
07522       {
07523         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf message-digest-key %d md5 %s",
07524              ck->key_id, ck->auth_key);
07525         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07526           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07527         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07528       }
07529     
07530     /* Interface Output Cost print. */
07531     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, output_cost_cmd))
07532       {
07533         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf cost %u", params->output_cost_cmd);
07534         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07535           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07536         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07537       }
07538     
07539     /* Hello Interval print. */
07540     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, v_hello) &&
07541         params->v_hello != OSPF_HELLO_INTERVAL_DEFAULT)
07542       {
07543         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf hello-interval %u", params->v_hello);
07544         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07545           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07546         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07547       }
07548     
07549     
07550     /* Router Dead Interval print. */
07551     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, v_wait) &&
07552         params->v_wait != OSPF_ROUTER_DEAD_INTERVAL_DEFAULT)
07553       {
07554         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf dead-interval ");
07555         
07556         /* fast hello ? */
07557         if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, fast_hello))
07558           vty_out (vty, "minimal hello-multiplier %d",
07559                    params->fast_hello);
07560             else
07561               vty_out (vty, "%u", params->v_wait);
07562             
07563         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07564           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07565         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07566       }
07567     
07568       /* Router Priority print. */
07569     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, priority) &&
07570         params->priority != OSPF_ROUTER_PRIORITY_DEFAULT)
07571       {
07572         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf priority %u", params->priority);
07573         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07574           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07575         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07576       }
07577     
07578     /* Retransmit Interval print. */
07579     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, retransmit_interval) &&
07580         params->retransmit_interval != OSPF_RETRANSMIT_INTERVAL_DEFAULT)
07581       {
07582         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf retransmit-interval %u",
07583              params->retransmit_interval);
07584         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07585           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07586         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07587       }
07588     
07589     /* Transmit Delay print. */
07590     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, transmit_delay) &&
07591         params->transmit_delay != OSPF_TRANSMIT_DELAY_DEFAULT)
07592       {
07593         vty_out (vty, " ip ospf transmit-delay %u", params->transmit_delay);
07594         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07595           vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07596         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07597       }
07598 
07599     /* MTU ignore print. */
07600     if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (params, mtu_ignore) &&
07601        params->mtu_ignore != OSPF_MTU_IGNORE_DEFAULT)
07602       {
07603         if (params->mtu_ignore == 0)
07604           vty_out (vty, " no ip ospf mtu-ignore");
07605         else
07606           vty_out (vty, " ip ospf mtu-ignore");
07607         if (params != IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp))
07608            vty_out (vty, " %s", inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4));
07609         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07610       }
07611 
07612 
07613     while (1)
07614       {
07615         if (rn == NULL)
07616           rn = route_top (IF_OIFS_PARAMS (ifp));
07617         else
07618           rn = route_next (rn);
07619 
07620         if (rn == NULL)
07621           break;
07622         params = rn->info;
07623         if (params != NULL)
07624           break;
07625       }
07626       } while (rn);
07627       
07628 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
07629       ospf_opaque_config_write_if (vty, ifp);
07630 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
07631     }
07632 
07633   return write;
07634 }
07635 
07636 static int
07637 config_write_network_area (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
07638 {
07639   struct route_node *rn;
07640   u_char buf[INET_ADDRSTRLEN];
07641 
07642   /* `network area' print. */
07643   for (rn = route_top (ospf->networks); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
07644     if (rn->info)
07645       {
07646     struct ospf_network *n = rn->info;
07647 
07648     memset (buf, 0, INET_ADDRSTRLEN);
07649 
07650     /* Create Area ID string by specified Area ID format. */
07651     if (n->format == OSPF_AREA_ID_FORMAT_ADDRESS)
07652       strncpy ((char *) buf, inet_ntoa (n->area_id), INET_ADDRSTRLEN);
07653     else
07654       sprintf ((char *) buf, "%lu", 
07655            (unsigned long int) ntohl (n->area_id.s_addr));
07656 
07657     /* Network print. */
07658     vty_out (vty, " network %s/%d area %s%s",
07659          inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4), rn->p.prefixlen,
07660          buf, VTY_NEWLINE);
07661       }
07662 
07663   return 0;
07664 }
07665 
07666 static int
07667 config_write_ospf_area (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
07668 {
07669   struct listnode *node;
07670   struct ospf_area *area;
07671   u_char buf[INET_ADDRSTRLEN];
07672 
07673   /* Area configuration print. */
07674   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->areas, node, area))
07675     {
07676       struct route_node *rn1;
07677 
07678       area_id2str ((char *) buf, INET_ADDRSTRLEN, area);
07679 
07680       if (area->auth_type != OSPF_AUTH_NULL)
07681     {
07682       if (area->auth_type == OSPF_AUTH_SIMPLE)
07683         vty_out (vty, " area %s authentication%s", buf, VTY_NEWLINE);
07684       else
07685         vty_out (vty, " area %s authentication message-digest%s",
07686              buf, VTY_NEWLINE);
07687     }
07688 
07689       if (area->shortcut_configured != OSPF_SHORTCUT_DEFAULT)
07690     vty_out (vty, " area %s shortcut %s%s", buf,
07691          ospf_shortcut_mode_str[area->shortcut_configured],
07692          VTY_NEWLINE);
07693 
07694       if ((area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_STUB)
07695       || (area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_NSSA)
07696       )
07697     {
07698       if (area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_STUB)
07699         vty_out (vty, " area %s stub", buf);
07700       else if (area->external_routing == OSPF_AREA_NSSA)
07701         {
07702           vty_out (vty, " area %s nssa", buf);
07703           switch (area->NSSATranslatorRole)
07704             {
07705               case OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_NEVER:
07706                 vty_out (vty, " translate-never");
07707                 break;
07708               case OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_ALWAYS:
07709                 vty_out (vty, " translate-always");
07710                 break;
07711               case OSPF_NSSA_ROLE_CANDIDATE:
07712               default:
07713                 vty_out (vty, " translate-candidate");
07714             }
07715         }
07716 
07717       if (area->no_summary)
07718         vty_out (vty, " no-summary");
07719 
07720       vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07721 
07722       if (area->default_cost != 1)
07723         vty_out (vty, " area %s default-cost %d%s", buf, 
07724              area->default_cost, VTY_NEWLINE);
07725     }
07726 
07727       for (rn1 = route_top (area->ranges); rn1; rn1 = route_next (rn1))
07728     if (rn1->info)
07729       {
07730         struct ospf_area_range *range = rn1->info;
07731 
07732         vty_out (vty, " area %s range %s/%d", buf,
07733              inet_ntoa (rn1->p.u.prefix4), rn1->p.prefixlen);
07734 
07735         if (range->cost_config != OSPF_AREA_RANGE_COST_UNSPEC)
07736           vty_out (vty, " cost %d", range->cost_config);
07737 
07738         if (!CHECK_FLAG (range->flags, OSPF_AREA_RANGE_ADVERTISE))
07739           vty_out (vty, " not-advertise");
07740 
07741         if (CHECK_FLAG (range->flags, OSPF_AREA_RANGE_SUBSTITUTE))
07742           vty_out (vty, " substitute %s/%d",
07743                inet_ntoa (range->subst_addr), range->subst_masklen);
07744 
07745         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07746       }
07747 
07748       if (EXPORT_NAME (area))
07749     vty_out (vty, " area %s export-list %s%s", buf,
07750          EXPORT_NAME (area), VTY_NEWLINE);
07751 
07752       if (IMPORT_NAME (area))
07753     vty_out (vty, " area %s import-list %s%s", buf,
07754          IMPORT_NAME (area), VTY_NEWLINE);
07755 
07756       if (PREFIX_NAME_IN (area))
07757     vty_out (vty, " area %s filter-list prefix %s in%s", buf,
07758          PREFIX_NAME_IN (area), VTY_NEWLINE);
07759 
07760       if (PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area))
07761     vty_out (vty, " area %s filter-list prefix %s out%s", buf,
07762          PREFIX_NAME_OUT (area), VTY_NEWLINE);
07763     }
07764 
07765   return 0;
07766 }
07767 
07768 static int
07769 config_write_ospf_nbr_nbma (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
07770 {
07771   struct ospf_nbr_nbma *nbr_nbma;
07772   struct route_node *rn;
07773 
07774   /* Static Neighbor configuration print. */
07775   for (rn = route_top (ospf->nbr_nbma); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
07776     if ((nbr_nbma = rn->info))
07777       {
07778     vty_out (vty, " neighbor %s", inet_ntoa (nbr_nbma->addr));
07779 
07780     if (nbr_nbma->priority != OSPF_NEIGHBOR_PRIORITY_DEFAULT)
07781       vty_out (vty, " priority %d", nbr_nbma->priority);
07782 
07783     if (nbr_nbma->v_poll != OSPF_POLL_INTERVAL_DEFAULT)
07784       vty_out (vty, " poll-interval %d", nbr_nbma->v_poll);
07785 
07786     vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07787       }
07788 
07789   return 0;
07790 }
07791 
07792 static int
07793 config_write_virtual_link (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
07794 {
07795   struct listnode *node;
07796   struct ospf_vl_data *vl_data;
07797   u_char buf[INET_ADDRSTRLEN];
07798 
07799   /* Virtual-Link print */
07800   for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->vlinks, node, vl_data))
07801     {
07802       struct listnode *n2;
07803       struct crypt_key *ck;
07804       struct ospf_interface *oi;
07805 
07806       if (vl_data != NULL)
07807     {
07808       memset (buf, 0, INET_ADDRSTRLEN);
07809       
07810       if (vl_data->format == OSPF_AREA_ID_FORMAT_ADDRESS)
07811         strncpy ((char *) buf, inet_ntoa (vl_data->vl_area_id), INET_ADDRSTRLEN);
07812       else
07813         sprintf ((char *) buf, "%lu", 
07814              (unsigned long int) ntohl (vl_data->vl_area_id.s_addr));
07815       oi = vl_data->vl_oi;
07816 
07817       /* timers */
07818       if (OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, v_hello) != OSPF_HELLO_INTERVAL_DEFAULT ||
07819           OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, v_wait) != OSPF_ROUTER_DEAD_INTERVAL_DEFAULT ||
07820           OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, retransmit_interval) != OSPF_RETRANSMIT_INTERVAL_DEFAULT ||
07821           OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, transmit_delay) != OSPF_TRANSMIT_DELAY_DEFAULT)
07822         vty_out (vty, " area %s virtual-link %s hello-interval %d retransmit-interval %d transmit-delay %d dead-interval %d%s",
07823              buf,
07824              inet_ntoa (vl_data->vl_peer), 
07825              OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, v_hello),
07826              OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, retransmit_interval),
07827              OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, transmit_delay),
07828              OSPF_IF_PARAM (oi, v_wait),
07829              VTY_NEWLINE);
07830       else
07831         vty_out (vty, " area %s virtual-link %s%s", buf,
07832              inet_ntoa (vl_data->vl_peer), VTY_NEWLINE);
07833       /* Auth key */
07834       if (IF_DEF_PARAMS (vl_data->vl_oi->ifp)->auth_simple[0] != '\0')
07835         vty_out (vty, " area %s virtual-link %s authentication-key %s%s",
07836              buf,
07837              inet_ntoa (vl_data->vl_peer),
07838              IF_DEF_PARAMS (vl_data->vl_oi->ifp)->auth_simple,
07839              VTY_NEWLINE);
07840       /* md5 keys */
07841       for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (IF_DEF_PARAMS (vl_data->vl_oi->ifp)->auth_crypt,
07842                                      n2, ck))
07843             vty_out (vty, " area %s virtual-link %s"
07844                      " message-digest-key %d md5 %s%s",
07845                      buf,
07846                      inet_ntoa (vl_data->vl_peer),
07847                      ck->key_id, ck->auth_key, VTY_NEWLINE);
07848      
07849     }
07850     }
07851 
07852   return 0;
07853 }
07854 
07855 
07856 static int
07857 config_write_ospf_redistribute (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
07858 {
07859   int type;
07860 
07861   /* redistribute print. */
07862   for (type = 0; type < ZEBRA_ROUTE_MAX; type++)
07863     if (type != zclient->redist_default && zclient->redist[type])
07864       {
07865         vty_out (vty, " redistribute %s", zebra_route_string(type));
07866     if (ospf->dmetric[type].value >= 0)
07867       vty_out (vty, " metric %d", ospf->dmetric[type].value);
07868     
07869         if (ospf->dmetric[type].type == EXTERNAL_METRIC_TYPE_1)
07870       vty_out (vty, " metric-type 1");
07871 
07872     if (ROUTEMAP_NAME (ospf, type))
07873       vty_out (vty, " route-map %s", ROUTEMAP_NAME (ospf, type));
07874     
07875         vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07876       }
07877 
07878   return 0;
07879 }
07880 
07881 static int
07882 config_write_ospf_default_metric (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
07883 {
07884   if (ospf->default_metric != -1)
07885     vty_out (vty, " default-metric %d%s", ospf->default_metric,
07886          VTY_NEWLINE);
07887   return 0;
07888 }
07889 
07890 static int
07891 config_write_ospf_distribute (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
07892 {
07893   int type;
07894 
07895   if (ospf)
07896     {
07897       /* distribute-list print. */
07898       for (type = 0; type < ZEBRA_ROUTE_MAX; type++)
07899     if (ospf->dlist[type].name)
07900       vty_out (vty, " distribute-list %s out %s%s", 
07901            ospf->dlist[type].name,
07902            zebra_route_string(type), VTY_NEWLINE);
07903 
07904       /* default-information print. */
07905       if (ospf->default_originate != DEFAULT_ORIGINATE_NONE)
07906     {
07907       vty_out (vty, " default-information originate");
07908       if (ospf->default_originate == DEFAULT_ORIGINATE_ALWAYS)
07909         vty_out (vty, " always");
07910 
07911       if (ospf->dmetric[DEFAULT_ROUTE].value >= 0)
07912         vty_out (vty, " metric %d",
07913              ospf->dmetric[DEFAULT_ROUTE].value);
07914       if (ospf->dmetric[DEFAULT_ROUTE].type == EXTERNAL_METRIC_TYPE_1)
07915         vty_out (vty, " metric-type 1");
07916 
07917       if (ROUTEMAP_NAME (ospf, DEFAULT_ROUTE))
07918         vty_out (vty, " route-map %s",
07919              ROUTEMAP_NAME (ospf, DEFAULT_ROUTE));
07920       
07921       vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07922     }
07923 
07924     }
07925 
07926   return 0;
07927 }
07928 
07929 static int
07930 config_write_ospf_distance (struct vty *vty, struct ospf *ospf)
07931 {
07932   struct route_node *rn;
07933   struct ospf_distance *odistance;
07934 
07935   if (ospf->distance_all)
07936     vty_out (vty, " distance %d%s", ospf->distance_all, VTY_NEWLINE);
07937 
07938   if (ospf->distance_intra 
07939       || ospf->distance_inter 
07940       || ospf->distance_external)
07941     {
07942       vty_out (vty, " distance ospf");
07943 
07944       if (ospf->distance_intra)
07945     vty_out (vty, " intra-area %d", ospf->distance_intra);
07946       if (ospf->distance_inter)
07947     vty_out (vty, " inter-area %d", ospf->distance_inter);
07948       if (ospf->distance_external)
07949     vty_out (vty, " external %d", ospf->distance_external);
07950 
07951       vty_out (vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07952     }
07953   
07954   for (rn = route_top (ospf->distance_table); rn; rn = route_next (rn))
07955     if ((odistance = rn->info) != NULL)
07956       {
07957     vty_out (vty, " distance %d %s/%d %s%s", odistance->distance,
07958          inet_ntoa (rn->p.u.prefix4), rn->p.prefixlen,
07959          odistance->access_list ? odistance->access_list : "",
07960          VTY_NEWLINE);
07961       }
07962   return 0;
07963 }
07964 
07965 /* OSPF configuration write function. */
07966 static int
07967 ospf_config_write (struct vty *vty)
07968 {
07969   struct ospf *ospf;
07970   struct interface *ifp;
07971   struct ospf_interface *oi;
07972   struct listnode *node;
07973   int write = 0;
07974 
07975   ospf = ospf_lookup ();
07976   if (ospf != NULL)
07977     {
07978       /* `router ospf' print. */
07979       vty_out (vty, "router ospf%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
07980 
07981       write++;
07982 
07983       if (!ospf->networks)
07984         return write;
07985 
07986       /* Router ID print. */
07987       if (ospf->router_id_static.s_addr != 0)
07988         vty_out (vty, " ospf router-id %s%s",
07989                  inet_ntoa (ospf->router_id_static), VTY_NEWLINE);
07990 
07991       /* ABR type print. */
07992       if (ospf->abr_type != OSPF_ABR_DEFAULT)
07993         vty_out (vty, " ospf abr-type %s%s", 
07994                  ospf_abr_type_str[ospf->abr_type], VTY_NEWLINE);
07995 
07996       /* log-adjacency-changes flag print. */
07997       if (CHECK_FLAG(ospf->config, OSPF_LOG_ADJACENCY_CHANGES))
07998     {
07999       vty_out(vty, " log-adjacency-changes");
08000       if (CHECK_FLAG(ospf->config, OSPF_LOG_ADJACENCY_DETAIL))
08001         vty_out(vty, " detail");
08002       vty_out(vty, "%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
08003     }
08004 
08005       /* RFC1583 compatibility flag print -- Compatible with CISCO 12.1. */
08006       if (CHECK_FLAG (ospf->config, OSPF_RFC1583_COMPATIBLE))
08007     vty_out (vty, " compatible rfc1583%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
08008 
08009       /* auto-cost reference-bandwidth configuration.  */
08010       if (ospf->ref_bandwidth != OSPF_DEFAULT_REF_BANDWIDTH)
08011         {
08012           vty_out (vty, "! Important: ensure reference bandwidth "
08013                         "is consistent across all routers%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
08014           vty_out (vty, " auto-cost reference-bandwidth %d%s",
08015            ospf->ref_bandwidth / 1000, VTY_NEWLINE);
08016         }
08017 
08018       /* SPF timers print. */
08019       if (ospf->spf_delay != OSPF_SPF_DELAY_DEFAULT ||
08020       ospf->spf_holdtime != OSPF_SPF_HOLDTIME_DEFAULT ||
08021       ospf->spf_max_holdtime != OSPF_SPF_MAX_HOLDTIME_DEFAULT)
08022     vty_out (vty, " timers throttle spf %d %d %d%s",
08023          ospf->spf_delay, ospf->spf_holdtime,
08024          ospf->spf_max_holdtime, VTY_NEWLINE);
08025       
08026       /* Max-metric router-lsa print */
08027       config_write_stub_router (vty, ospf);
08028       
08029       /* SPF refresh parameters print. */
08030       if (ospf->lsa_refresh_interval != OSPF_LSA_REFRESH_INTERVAL_DEFAULT)
08031     vty_out (vty, " refresh timer %d%s",
08032          ospf->lsa_refresh_interval, VTY_NEWLINE);
08033 
08034       /* Redistribute information print. */
08035       config_write_ospf_redistribute (vty, ospf);
08036 
08037       /* passive-interface print. */
08038       if (ospf->passive_interface_default == OSPF_IF_PASSIVE)
08039         vty_out (vty, " passive-interface default%s", VTY_NEWLINE);
08040       
08041       for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (om->iflist, node, ifp))
08042         if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp), passive_interface)
08043             && IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->passive_interface != 
08044                               ospf->passive_interface_default)
08045           {
08046             vty_out (vty, " %spassive-interface %s%s",
08047                      IF_DEF_PARAMS (ifp)->passive_interface ? "" : "no ",
08048                      ifp->name, VTY_NEWLINE);
08049           }
08050       for (ALL_LIST_ELEMENTS_RO (ospf->oiflist, node, oi))
08051         {
08052           if (!OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (oi->params, passive_interface))
08053             continue;
08054           if (OSPF_IF_PARAM_CONFIGURED (IF_DEF_PARAMS (oi->ifp),
08055                                         passive_interface))
08056             {
08057               if (oi->params->passive_interface == IF_DEF_PARAMS (oi->ifp)->passive_interface)
08058                 continue;
08059             }
08060           else if (oi->params->passive_interface == ospf->passive_interface_default)
08061             continue;
08062           
08063           vty_out (vty, " %spassive-interface %s %s%s",
08064                    oi->params->passive_interface ? "" : "no ",
08065                    oi->ifp->name,
08066                    inet_ntoa (oi->address->u.prefix4), VTY_NEWLINE);
08067         }
08068       
08069       /* Network area print. */
08070       config_write_network_area (vty, ospf);
08071 
08072       /* Area config print. */
08073       config_write_ospf_area (vty, ospf);
08074 
08075       /* static neighbor print. */
08076       config_write_ospf_nbr_nbma (vty, ospf);
08077 
08078       /* Virtual-Link print. */
08079       config_write_virtual_link (vty, ospf);
08080 
08081       /* Default metric configuration.  */
08082       config_write_ospf_default_metric (vty, ospf);
08083 
08084       /* Distribute-list and default-information print. */
08085       config_write_ospf_distribute (vty, ospf);
08086 
08087       /* Distance configuration. */
08088       config_write_ospf_distance (vty, ospf);
08089 
08090 #ifdef HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA
08091       ospf_opaque_config_write_router (vty, ospf);
08092 #endif /* HAVE_OPAQUE_LSA */
08093     }
08094 
08095   return write;
08096 }
08097 
08098 void
08099 ospf_vty_show_init (void)
08100 {
08101   /* "show ip ospf" commands. */
08102   install_element (VIEW_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_cmd);
08103   install_element (ENABLE_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_cmd);
08104 
08105   /* "show ip ospf database" commands. */
08106   install_element (VIEW_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_cmd);
08107   install_element (VIEW_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_id_cmd);
08108   install_element (VIEW_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_id_adv_router_cmd);
08109   install_element (VIEW_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_adv_router_cmd);
08110   install_element (VIEW_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_id_self_cmd);
08111   install_element (VIEW_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_self_cmd);
08112   install_element (VIEW_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_cmd);
08113   install_element (ENABLE_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_cmd);
08114   install_element (ENABLE_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_id_cmd);
08115   install_element (ENABLE_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_id_adv_router_cmd);
08116   install_element (ENABLE_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_adv_router_cmd);
08117   install_element (ENABLE_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_id_self_cmd);
08118   install_element (ENABLE_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_type_self_cmd);
08119   install_element (ENABLE_NODE, &show_ip_ospf_database_cmd);
08120
